title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put butter over top in center of dish. Place in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth. Blend in nuts.
Pour in butter dish or pan.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Mix together.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cream of tartar in medium saucepan.
Add water, food coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan when mixture forms a ball and place on floured surface.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: cottage cheese
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper to taste. Pineapple (optional).

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix milk and water; scald.
Cool to 80°.
Add yeast and vanilla; stir until well mixed.
Add to egg mixture.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Place dough in warm place (80°).
Allow to rise 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down; allow to rise 15 minutes more.

title: river road cushaw
directions: Cut, cook and scrape squash.
Mash squash in a large bowl. Mix in remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350° (until brown on top). Freezes well.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and sugar.
Now add 1/2 cup margarine, table syrup, milk and vanilla.
Beat two minutes.
Then add eggs.
Beat more and bake.
A really good spice cake.

title: baked deviled tomatoes
directions: Halve each tomato.
Place cut side up on baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and spread with mustard.
Finely chop the pepper, celery and onion; mix with melted butter and spoon over each tomato half.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger with seasoning, 1/2 cup water and olives. Line pie plate with crescent rolls. Add 3/4 cup crushed corn chips over crust. Add hamburger filling. Spread sour cream over hamburger.
Add Cheddar cheese. Add remaining corn chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: punch bowl trifle
directions: Drain the pineapple saving the juice.
Prepare cake batter as package says, using the juice instead of water.
Add some water if needed.
Bake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut cake into 1-inch squares.
Prepare the pudding by package directions.
Place 1/2 cake into punch bowl.
Top with half of the pudding, then 1/2 of each of the following:
pie filling, pineapple, banana, fruit cocktail, oranges, whip topping and coconut.
Then do the same again.
Cover and chill for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Serves 55.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix shortening and flour thoroughly in a bowl.
Stir in enough milk to make a soft puffy easy to roll dough.
(Too much milk makes dough sticky; not enough makes biscuits dry.)
Knead lightly 25 to 30 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake until brown.

title: fudge
directions: Mix and cook the first 3 ingredients 7 to 8 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips. Dissolve.
Add marshmallows.
Dissolve.
Add nuts and mix well. Pour into a 10 x 15-inch pan until very firm.
Cut into squares. Yields 5 pounds.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix pudding powder with cream cheese.
Drain fruit and mix with cream cheese mixture.
Shape into ball and chill.

title: sweet potato-pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water and boil for 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add butter and pineapple to syrup mixture.
Pour over sweet potatoes in shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers fine; place on the bottom of dish. Combine the gelatine, milk, egg yolks and sugar; cook slowly, until slightly thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add whipping cream.
Place both mixtures in dish.
Top with crushed graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: five layer dessert
directions: Mix well and put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage about 7 minutes in boiling water. Drain. Alternate sliced apples and cooked cabbage in greased casserole. Add franks. Make sauce: Melt butter and stir in cornstarch. Then stir in sugar, water, vinegar and salt. Pour over cabbage mixture. Bake for 1 hour.

title: english brown stew
directions: Brown meat in margarine with flour.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and pearl onions.

title: pumpkin soup(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons of the butter until foamy.
Add onions and saute until limp.
Sprinkle with flour.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes, then gradually add chicken stock.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add pumpkin puree, seasonings and half and half.
Reheat, without boiling, and adjust seasonings to taste. Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon butter until just melted.
Serve immediately, topped with croutons.

title: white bread
directions: Mix all in bowl, then let rise until double in size.
Work out, then put in pans.
Let rise again, then bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender.
Cook spaghetti as directed until just before it is completely tender.
Add chicken and spaghetti to sauce.
Top with Parmesan, if desired.

title: microwave parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg, then coat with dry mixture.
Cook covered on High for 15 minutes.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni in single layer over one-half of each breadstick.
Fold remaining half of breadstick over top.
Seal ends and twist. Place on ungreased cookie pan.

title: cottontail milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into glasses and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine white sugar, powdered sugar, oleo and oil.
Beat well. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add finely cut nuts, if desired.
Add all to mixture. Make small balls; place on a cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork or finger.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water, add frozen strawberries; mash and add cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple. Mix together and put in a bowl.
Refrigerate until set.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in a buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Arrange asparagus over rice.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and half of the cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 6.

title: summer tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as according to package.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles, tuna, celery and onions.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half the mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the zucchini and squash.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese and parsley. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Sprinkle with diced tomato.

title: pat's pasta con broccoli
directions: Saute butter, sliced mushrooms and diced garlic.
Steam broccoli until tender, then add to mushroom mixture.
Simmer while shells are cooking.
Add shells, whipping cream, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese to mixture.
Simmer until cream thickens.
May add a little half and half cream when reheating.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Combine zucchini, olive oil and garlic in a skillet.
Sprinkle with pepper and oregano.
Cover and cook over medium heat until steamed through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove lid; reduce heat and simmer until zucchini is tender.
At serving time, sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrots a la orange
directions: Slice carrots crosswise on the bias, about 1 inch thick.
Cook, covered in boiling salted water, until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute or more.
Stir in butter until melted.
Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.
Turn into serving dish.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Lightly grease skins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cut thin slices off top of potatoes. Scoop out inside and mash.
Add onion, eggs, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese, margarine, salt, pepper and enough hot milk to desired consistency. Beat until fluffy.
Carefully pile mixture into potato shells.
Brush tops with additional margarine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carol's chicken combo sandwiches
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Wrap each in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can make and refrigerate and then bake when ready to serve.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine in skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until coconut is toasted and golden brown. Press into 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Chill.

title: breakfast topping
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over hot cakes, waffles or French toast.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix all together; put in pie crusts. Top with 1 container of Cool Whip. Put in icebox and cool for 25 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and flavoring.
Serve over pound cake or other dessert. Yields 2 cups.

title: luscious banana layer cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder, soda and salt. Sift together three times.
Cream butter, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well, then add bananas and beat again.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla.
Bake in two greased pans in a moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.
Use a lemon filling between layers and any desired frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until hot.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Then add melted margarine, coconut and flavoring.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue (same as used on Easy Chocolate Pie).
Sprinkle with coconut and brown topping.

title: georgian brunswick stew
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large dutch oven, bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add chicken and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from broth, reserving broth in Dutch oven.
Cool meat; bone and coarsely chop.
Set aside.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients to broth; bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in meat, corn, beans, peas, potatoes and vinegar.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring often.
Add okra; cook 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaves. Yields 6 1/2 quarts.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and diced cheese.
Cover and let simmer until cheese is melted.
Stir until well blended.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain lasagna or macaroni.
Fry sausage; drain and crumble fine.
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Add tomatoes and cook until most of liquid is gone.
Layer macaroni, sausage, sauce and cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly at 350°.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Parboil the yams, pare and slice.
Peel and slice the apples. Mix together the cornstarch, sugar and apple juice.
Add the butter and lemon juice.
Alternate layers of sliced yams and apples in a buttered casserole.
Pour the sauce over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream fettucine
directions: Melt margarine and saute garlic and parsley.
Add remainder of ingredients, except noodles.
Heat over low heat.
Toss with cooked pasta.

title: cottage cheese cake
directions: Put into blender and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Makes 2.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: potatoes with rosemary
directions: Heat olive oil and minced garlic in 10-inch heavy skillet over low heat until garlic starts to sizzle, about 10 minutes. Add potatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and tiny pinch rosemary; toss to coat.
Increase heat to medium and cook, covered, until potatoes are tender when pierced, about 15 minutes.
Uncover skillet.

Increase heat to high and cook, stirring frequently, until well browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining rosemary and additional salt and pepper. Any leftovers make ideal additions to beef or turkey hash.

title: zucchini ole
directions: Put zucchini in a skillet.
Cover with salsa (no other liquid).
Cover and cook on low until fork tender.
Remove from heat, cover with cheese, replace skillet cover for about 1 minute until cheese melts.
Serve.
This can be made in any amount.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Great served with cornbread, especially broccoli cornbread.
This soup is quick, easy and makes a lot.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Fry bacon and chop into small bits.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix bacon, ground beef and onion in frying pan.
Add golden mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles to desired taste.
Just prior to serving, mix in sour cream with meat mixture until warm.
Serve sauce over the noodles.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients (mixture will be thick) and spread in pan.
Mix next three ingredients; pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or less (when top is evenly browned).

title: nibbles
directions: In plastic bag add all ingredients.
Shake well to blend.
Zap for 1 minute in a microwave.
Shake bag again.
Zap for 1 minute more.
Let cool.
Store in a plastic bag or airtight container.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Mix hamburger, chopped onion, beaten egg, bread slices wet with water and squeezed out, and garlic; mix well.
Roll in small balls; fry in hot grease.
When brown, drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and 2 cans water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti to serve this over.

title: crock-pot apple butter(very simple and tasty)
directions: Cook apples and cider in kettle 40 minutes.
Put through food mill.
Measure and put in crock-pot.
For each pint of pureed apples, add 1 cup sugar or sugar substitute, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon allspice and 1/2 teaspoon ground cloves.
Stir well. Turn crock-pot on high and cook 4 hours.
Take off lid and finish cooking (I cover with a spatter screen).
Cooks down faster after lid is removed.
Cook 4 to 4 1/2 hours more, stirring every two hours.
Put in jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes or can be frozen in small containers.

title: pineapple and graham squares
directions: Mix 2 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs with melted butter and press in a 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and cool.

title: coconut-caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add coconut and chopped pecans; cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set the mixture aside.
Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer one-fourth of cream cheese mixture in each pastry shell.
Drizzle one-fourth of caramel topping on each pie.
Sprinkle one-fourth of coconut-pecan mixture evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients; cover and freeze until firm.
Let frozen pies stand at room temperature 5 minutes before slicing.
Yield:
2 (9-inch) pies.
Rich, so may be cut in eighths.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil 3 cups water and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Set aside to cool. In a large bowl combine:
1 cup water, maraschino cherries, pineapple and bananas.
Add sugar water and freeze (at least overnight).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, pecans, flour and brown sugar; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken for company
directions: Butter baking pan and place chicken breasts in pan for bottom layer.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over.
Mix dry onion soup in salad dressing and pour over chicken.
Add apricot preserves for next layer and spread evenly.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
During last 10 minutes of baking, add a layer of mandarin oranges and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Wash
and remove pits from the peaches.
Peaches should be green
and	firm.
Mix
brown sugar, water, Hawaiian salt, five spice
powder and cider vinegar together in a large pot; cook until
it
boils.
Add li hing mui; mix together.
Cool. Mix
with cut up peaches; store in sterilized jars.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate.
Let set overnight for best flavor.

title: beef broth with pastina
directions: Combine the broth and pastina in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover tightly and cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes, or until boiling.
Let the soup stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
For 1 serving:
Combine 1/2 cup beef broth and 1/2 ounce dry pastina in a serving bowl.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 1 to 3 minutes, or until boiling.
Let it stand for 2 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese dish
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mix cheese and pineapple.
Mix butter and juice.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
(I cook in a 2 1/2-quart Corning Ware dish.)

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla for 15 minutes in Mixmaster.
Pour into graham cracker crust; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 12 pieces.
Peel onions and slice finely. Peel and crush garlic.
Fry onions, garlic and salt until golden. Add chicken and fry gently.
Take pot off heat.
Add paprika and pepper to taste.
Return to heat and add a wine glass of water. Bring to boil; cover pot tightly and stew gently 50 to 60 minutes. Add liquid as necessary, to keep from boiling dry.
Turn up heat and remove lid at the end.
Remove from heat and serve just before all liquid boils away.
Serve with noodles.
For richness, sour cream may be added in the last 5 minutes.

title: mary's blonde brownies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Make a crumb mixture. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put crumb mixture in the bottom of the pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Brown meat and onion; drain. Stir in macaroni and next 5 ingredients.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with corn chips before serving.

title: cauliflower bacon strata
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon bacon drippings until tender.
Arrange bread slices in dish.
Top with onion, cheese, cauliflower and bacon slices.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bacon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: chunky chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar in blender.
Slowly add the oil.
Stir in poppy seed.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: french bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups bread flour, yeast and salt.
Add warm water and beat at low speed 30 seconds with mixer beaters.
Scrape bowl constantly.
Then beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in as much flour as possible using a wooden spoon to make a stiff dough that is smooth and elastic.
Knead on floured surface by hand 5 to 10 minutes.
Shape in a ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Turn to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn on lightly floured surface.

title: asparagus tips with mushroom sauce
directions: Drain asparagus and reserve liquid.
Spread asparagus in bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine mushroom soup with enough liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until casserole is bubbly.

title: fried tomatoes and creamy gravy
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Coat tomatoes with mixture.
Fry until golden brown in bacon drippings, turning once.
Remove slices from pan and place on platter to keep warm.
Over medium to low heat, warm cream and salt, adding 1 to 2 tablespoons cornmeal mixture as needed to thicken gravy.
Serve bacon, tomatoes and gravy over English muffins.
Serves 6.

title: ronald reagan's macaroni and cheese(quick and tasty!)
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a double boiler, then mix with milk (about 1/2 cup).
Add spices.
Cook macaroni per package instructions.
Drain.

title: low-fat chicken delite(for family of four)
directions: Mix honey and barbecue sauce.
Lay chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: triple-orange ambrosia salad
directions: Pour boiling liquid over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add orange sherbet.
Stir until melted. Stir in 1/2 of mandarin orange segments.
Pour in 6-cup ring mold. Chill until firm.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup broth and vegetables and cook about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple fancy salad
directions: Mix by hand.
(Do not beat.)
Add chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve or place in shallow pans.
Freeze.
Cut
into squares at serving time.
Can be served with pineapple slices and orange garnishes.
Serves 50.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Spread mixture over cooled pie shell that has already been cooked. Place 1 pint strawberries in bottom (slice and lay flat).
Then put 1 pint strawberries, sugar and cornstarch in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Spray pan with Pam and heat until mixture is smooth and thick.
It should take about 10 minutes.
Be sure to stir constantly.
Mixture will be clear.
Cool.
Pour over berries in pie dish.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cinderella cake
directions: Mix oats and water and let stand.
Stir margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix in raisins, pecans and coconut. Chop cherries and add to mixture.
Add condensed milk and mix thoroughly.
(Best if mixed with hands.)
Pack into a wax paper lined loaf pan.
Garnish top by sprinkling on a layer of coconut, then arranging cherry and pecan halves in a decorative pattern. Refrigerate until served.

title: pickled eggs & red beets
directions: Combine the brown sugar, vinegar, water, cinnamon and cloves. Boil together for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool. Add beets and eggs to the liquid. Let stand for at least 24 hours in the refrigerator in a glass jar.

title: scallops in wine
directions: Saute scallops in butter in large skillet 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove scallops from skillet, reserving drippings.
Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic 3 to 5 minutes; remove vegetables, reserving drippings.
Add wine, juices and seasonings to skillet. Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in scallops and vegetables. Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot vermicelli and garnish, if desired.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into small balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Put in greased pan 2-inches apart (they spread) and bake at 350° to 375° about 12 minutes.

title: consomme rice
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° around 1 hour, when liquid gets absorbed, stir and add maybe 1/4 can of water.
Finish cooking until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Add just enough mayonnaise to toss.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn, corn and more corn
directions: Mix all together and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake for about 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve hot.

title: delicious muddy mix
directions: Measure cereal in large bowl.
In a small saucepan over low heat melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Remove crust and roll bread flat with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese and dry minced onion on slices.
Cut in half and wrap in bacon strip.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped scallops 2
directions: Wash scallops.
If large scallops, cut into smaller pieces. It is better to use smaller, sweeter bay scallops.
Melt butter; mix with all crumbs.
Alternate layers of scallops with crumbs in buttered, shallow ovenproof dish.
Pour cream over top, covering all areas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on individual shells as a first course, as a main dish or on a buffet table.
If you double the recipe, do not fully double the amount of cream.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and slice potato.
Cook in a covered saucepan with a little water until tender.
Add other ingredients and beat with mixer until creamy.
Fill unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until edge of crust is brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice, drain.
Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain.
Mix rice and broccoli and spread in casserole dish.
Mix Cheez Whiz and soups, then spread on top of rice and broccoli.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large frypan, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add the chicken pieces, sprinkling garlic powder over the chicken.
Saute 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned.

title: cottage cheese patties, saxonian style
directions: Shape by hand into little patties and fry in your pan with olive oil.
When golden brown, sprinkle with sugar.
Have hot coffee!
Happy Eating!

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and granulated sugar until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture.
(This makes a very stiff dough that should be mixed with hands.)
Put in a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch cake pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees in oblong pan or 1 1/2 hours in tube pan at 350 degrees.

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Set corn out to thaw for at least 2 hours.
Melt butter under medium heat (do not brown) in large skillet or frying pan.
Add cayenne, black pepper and liquid smoke.
Add corn and grill on high heat until corn is sweet and slightly tender (it is important for the corn to taste young, not overcooked like cream corn).
Add lime juice, tarragon and cream.
Stir for an additional 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and serve.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Pan-fry onions in the butter.
Stir in the flour, the sugar, the salt and the pepper.
Cook until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in the tomato juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute. Stir hot tomato mixture gradually into the cold milk.
Heat rapidly to serving temperature.
Serve immediately.

title: weight watchers soup(fat burning soup)
directions: Cut vegetables in small pieces and cover with water.
Boil hard for 10 minutes.
Cut to simmer and continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Add remainder of ingredients.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a large bowl, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Set mixture aside.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken; skin and debone and tear into pieces.
Thaw or steam broccoli.
Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Layer with chicken pieces; sprinkle with sliced mushrooms. Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sherry and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt butter; mix in bread crumbs and parsley.
Sprinkle a small amount of grated cheese (about 1/4 cup), then sprinkle bread crumb mixture on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: liver and onions with gravy
directions: Lightly salt and pepper liver. Coat with flour, not flour for gravy.
In a large skillet, brown one side of liver on medium heat.
Remove and place on plate.
Place onion in skillet with oil and brown a little, then remove and place on plate.
Add flour (for gravy) to oil.
Stir.
Add water to flour and oil.
Stir well.
Place liver in skillet, unbrowned side down.
Put onion on top and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 25 minutes or until gravy is thickness you like.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. In mixing bowl, beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light.
Add eggs and milk, beating until smooth.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In saucepan, add
all ingredients.
Cook over low flame until spreading consistency.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; cream, then add oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda and flavorings.
Let set in refrigerator 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Roll in balls and press down with a glass that has been dipped in water one time only then dipped in sugar each time you press down the ball.
Bake at 375°.

title: caramel sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In each of 12 muffin pan cups, place 2 teaspoons each
of butter and brown sugar.
Place in oven to melt. Mix remaining ingredients except pecan halves in bowl, beating vigorously 1/2 minute.

title: schoolhouse soup
directions: Simmer rice and vegetables in chicken broth being sure to have 2 cups broth remaining when rice is tender.
Water may have to be added.
Add seasonings, cooked chicken and milk.
Bring to boiling point but do not boil.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into large bowl.
Chill two hours.
Garnish with 1/2 cup chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: hot and sweet pepper jelly
directions: You will also need 3 (6 ounce) decorative jars with lids.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sugar, cocoa and salt) first.
Add milk, vanilla, eggs and melted margarine to the dry mixture.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour the mixture evenly into the 3 pie shells.
Add extra chopped pecans to each pie until the nuts cover the entire surface of each pie (make sure the pecans are mixed in with the pie filling, not just lying on top of the pie).
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all but soup and dressing.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Spread soup over top.
Put dressing mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pina colada pineapple pie
directions: Mix well the nuts, pineapple, milk and lemon juice.
Add the Cool Whip.
Stir well and pour into graham cracker crust. Cover top with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Butter both sides of the bread. Line bottom of a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage and mushrooms over bread.
Top with cheese.

title: german coconut bundt cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/4 c. salad oil over low heat; cool.
Beat eggs; add sugars and remaining salad oil; beat 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate mixture, vanilla and coconut extract.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture, along with milk.
Fold in coconut.
Turn into greased and floured bundt pan or 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until it tests done.
Remove from oven; with fork poke holes to cover surface.
Spoon on Butter Sauce; cool on rack 1 hour.
Remove from pan; dust top with powdered sugar.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Make into balls; chill.
Heat until melted in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate; place on wax paper.

title: cherry cakes
directions: Roll
in
small
balls.
Press down in pan with a fork. Bake in	a moderate oven (350°).
Put a little white icing on top of each and a cherry.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt chocolate bits and spread on cooked batter.
Sprinkle with nuts and cut into squares.

title: old fashioned bean soup(in memory of my dad, glen martin)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot, cover and cook on high 5-6 hours, and on low cook 10-12 hours.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
In saucepan combine margarine, water and cocoa, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over med heat.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 2 inch baking pan or dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: toasted buttered pecans
directions: Spread pecans evenly in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine melted butter, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and powdered sugar, stir until well blended.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour alternately with whipping cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Stir.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh cream corn
directions: Cut corn off cob. Scrape cob to get extra juices. Boil corn until tender. Drain most of water. Add butter, salt and pepper. In cup, combine water and cornstarch until smooth. Add to corn and cook on low until creamy.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In pan, melt butter and stir in crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
In bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stir in condensed milk and undrained strawberries.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour in prepared pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.

title: lemon delight
directions: Press evenly in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in additional sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet until firm.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: baked country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in cold water to cover; scrub well with brush.
Place in roasting pan.
Add 5 cups water to pan; cover tightly with lid or heavy foil.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven on, set at 500°.
After temperature is reached (watch oven signal), bake ham for 10 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Do not open oven.
Let stand 3 hours.
Heat oven to 500° again; bake 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave overnight (or about 10 to 12 hours) without opening oven door.
Next day, remove ham from roasting pan, remove skin and trim fat to desired thickness.
Score fat and place on rack in baking pan.
Glaze.

title: chicken and savory biscuits
directions: In medium bowl, mix baking mix, thyme, black pepper, and 1/2 c. milk until well blended.

title: better than homemade tortellini soup
directions: Take the chicken and cut it along both sides of the spine. Keep the spine and place on a sheet pan. Next, cut the chicken in the center of the breasts, cracking the two apart. (Careful not to cut yourself in the process.) Carefully remove the breast meat from the bone. Now you should have two halves of chicken. Next, cut each half in half at the base of the rib cage above the thigh. Look for the joint and try to cut in between bones. Now you have four quarters. Carefully stand the leg up and cut along the bone, removing the meat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's and drop in bowl with lid.
Put in cinnamon and sugar.
Put on lid.
Shake well.
Put in Bundt pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, milk, eggs, margarine, salt and vanilla.
Mix together well and bake for 20 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: easy granola mix
directions: Mix oats, wheat germ, coconut, brown sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add maple syrup and mix well. Stir together melted butter and vanilla and mix in the mixture. Turn into a large shallow pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes. Cool. Add raisins and/or nuts. Store in airtight container.

title: shrimp fettucini alfredo
directions: Boil fettucini noodles according to package directions. Drain well. Return to pan and add heavy cream to desired thickness.
Add 1 - 2 Tbsp butter.
Add shrimp and stir well. Return to low heat for ingredients to warm through.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chip deluxe cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat Crisco, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy. Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour, beating well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Bring to boil juice of 8 ounce can crushed pineapple.
Fill to 1 cup with water.
Add to liquid:
orange jello and cream cheese. Beat while hot; set aside for short time.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and carrots.
Chill until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add flavor, then flour.
Mixture will become stiff.
Add nuts.
May have to mix with spoon if too thick.
Roll dough into finger size logs.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 1 hour at 225°.
When done, let cool.
Roll each log in 4x sugar.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen depending on log size.

title: eggs delicious
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy in large mixing bowl.
Slowly beat in milk until well blended.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in ham, tomato, salt and pepper.
Place butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Heat on Full power for 30 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Add egg mixture.
Cook on Full power for 8 to 10 1/2 minutes or until eggs are set, yet still moist.
Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked brie
directions: On lined cookie sheet place Brie inside bread.
Cover Brie with brown sugar and nuts; a few dots of butter on top and bake about 15 minutes at 350°. Keep eye on it as you don't want the cheese melting too much to cook out.
Serve with fresh fruit: grapes, apples, etc.
Put crackers on side.

title: escarole and beans
directions: Boil escarole in water about 10 to 15 minutes.
Saute cut up bacon, onion and garlic.
Add can of cannellini beans, paprika and cooked escarole.
Mix together and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: round steak appetizer
directions: Slice the tenderized round steak into 2-inch strips.
Season with the salts.
Coat the strips with the flour.
Heat oil in electric skillet to approximately 400° to 425°.
Quickly fry the steak strips, browning well on each side in the hot oil.
Try and only turn the pieces once while frying.
Drain and cool on paper towels.
When strips are cool enough to handle, cut in approximately 2-inch squares.
Skewer the steak squares on toothpicks and serve with horseradish sauce for dipping.

title: baked brie
directions: Roll out two sheets of phyllo dough.
Place Brie on top. Sprinkle brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts on top of Brie. Fold pastry over Brie.
(Use excess pastry to decorate top.)

title: rozky(nut horns)
directions: Take flour, sugar and salt.
Work butter into flour mixture with fingers.
Crumble yeast into warm milk.
Add yolks with yeast mixture to flour.
Work together until dough sticks firm.
Place in refrigerator overnight. When ready to roll dough 1/4 inch thick spread filling, roll up dough and shape into crescent.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: yogurt fruit soup (low-fat)
directions: Puree all ingredients (except mint leaves) in a food processor or blender.
Chill thoroughly for at least 3 hours.
Garnish with mint leaves prior to serving.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Beat eggs fluffy. Add sugar gradually, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir in sifted dry ingredients. Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix well and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Beat eggs until stiff and dry.
Pour the cooked syrup over the whites and beat and beat!
Add pecans and vanilla.
Dip out by the spoonful onto greased platter.

title: party puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Over very low heat, stir in onion soup mix and pieces of biscuits.
Toss gently.
Place biscuits on a cookie sheet lined with brown paper and bake 5 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 40.

title: milky way cake
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter; add Milky Way bars.
Stir until melted.
Make cake according to package directions.
Stir in Milky Way mixture and nuts.
Pour into a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake according to package directions. Remove from pan when cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Best pound cake ever!

title: kay's pastry
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Makes a mess so take your rings off.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, bring the water to a boil.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Gradually stir in grits.
Lower heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Remove pan from heat; stir in butter and chilies.
Add 1 cup of cheese until melted.
Mix eggs with milk.
Stir into grits.
Pour grits into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1 hour. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour beef brisket
directions: Rub brisket with salt and pepper.
Put brisket in roasting pan.
Mix sugar, vinegar and catsup and pour over brisket.
Place onion slices on top and cover roaster with foil.
Place in a 325° oven.
Cook for 2 hours or until it begins to feel tender.
Let cool.
Place in refrigerator in sauce and let it sit for 7 to 10 days. Turn over in sauce every day or two.

title: peanut butter and chocolate rice krispies
directions: Melt sugar and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then Rice Krispies.
Pat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits in a double boiler over medium-low heat or melt chocolate in microwave.
Put on top of Rice Krispies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn in greased baking dish. Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over vegetables. Mix melted oleo with crushed crackers. Top casserole with cracker mixture and almonds. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: young chow's fried rice
directions: First, place 3 tablespoons of oil in a small amount of wok along with a fresh onion.
Then, add diced ham, chicken or shrimp. Mix together; stir until evenly hot.
Add other desired vegetables like carrots, celery or green peppers.

title: texas chili
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and brown beef in drippings for 5 minutes.
Place in crock-pot.
Stir bacon and remaining ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: meatballs & creamy gravy
directions: Brown ground beef and salt and pepper. Moisten slice of bread in water and tear into small pieces, add to ground beef. Add onions and form into balls. Brown meatballs in miracle whip. Add soup and water. Simmer all for about 1/2 hour. Recipe can be easily doubled.

title: lemon cake
directions: Take the angel food cake and mix with 1 can lemon pie filling. Mix together until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
When cake is cool, cover with the other can of pie filling.
Cover with the Cool Whip. Holds up good. Can be made a day ahead, but then refrigerate.

title: crock-pot barbecue beef
directions: Place ingredients in order given into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in all other ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Dip is good to put in crock-pot to keep warm while serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add sugar, baking soda, oregano, salt, bay leaf, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour, 1/2 of the hour uncovered.

title: grandmother's cookie press vanilla wafers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well, until smooth.
Use cookie press and form into shapes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned on top, at 400°.
Best if formed into flat ridged bars.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with dry Bisquick. Mix in the sausage until all is well blended. Shape in very small balls. Bake at 375° until lightly brown. I use about 3 1/2 cups Bisquick instead of the 4 cups.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Mix flour, 2 sticks butter and cream cheese. Chill 10 to 15 minutes. Pinch off small pieces and press out thin into small tart pans.

title: lemon fruit pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk. Stir in nuts and fruit cocktail. Chill in graham cracker crust. Slice bananas on top. Cover with whipped cream.

title: italian style lasagne
directions: In large cooking pot, place browned meat and onions.
Add tomato puree, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Mix well and add garlic powder, oregano, basil, bay leaves and parsley flakes.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Mix Ricotta cheese, small curd cottage cheese, Romano (grated fresh) and Mozzarella cheese (grated).
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Top and bottom layers must be sauce.
Layer sauce, noodles, cheeses, noodles, sauce, noodles and cheeses until mixture runs out.
Sprinkle top sauce layer generously with Parmesan cheese (fresh grated) and dot with Mozzarella.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: e-z peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla, butter and cocoa thoroughly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Mix together onion, oil, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Gently mix together potatoes and sour cream mixture.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, milk and sugar to a boil.
Cook 1/2 hour, stirring all the time with fork.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Cool down.
Add whipped cream to loosen rice mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: fat free french fries
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Cut into wedges.
Dip wedges into the egg whites and place on a nonstick baking sheet sprayed with vegetable spray.
Season with salt or salt free seasoning.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, pudding, margarine, egg, milk and baking powder.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Drain peaches well and layer over the batter.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and juice together until smooth.
Pour over the peaches to 1/4 inch from the sides of pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Brush chicken
with mustard, then roll in bread crumbs. Bake in
lightly
greased cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and buttermilk; beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Crumble crackers. Combine all ingredients. Make into patties. Pan fry.

title: wild onions
directions: Clean onions; chop and put in a large skillet.
Add water and cook until tender and water is gone.
Add shortening and eggs, beaten.
Cook until eggs are done.

title: lime snow
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill until it is the consistency of the unbeaten egg white.
Add egg white to gelatin and beat until fluffy and holds shape.
Pour into dishes and chill.
Top with Sauce.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine 3 cups sugar with milk in heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat until dissolved. Add butter, stirring to keep from scorching. Cook the 4 tablespoons sugar in saucepan until melted and browned. Add to sugar, milk and butter until blended. Cook for about 6 minutes. Remove from heat and beat with mixer at high speed until it reaches spreading consistency. Spread between layers and on top and sides of 3 layer cake.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 6 to 10 minutes, until onion rings are golden brown.

title: creamy strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter in small bowl; press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Place cottage cheese and 1/2 cup egg product in electric blender or food processor container; cover.
Blend until pureed, scraping down sides of container as necessary.
Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cottage cheese mixture, remaining egg product and extract in large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until smooth; pour over crust in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until puffed and set.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions. Drain off excess fat. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni according to directions; drain. Combine cooked macaroni and beef into large serving bowl.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut biscuits into fourths using kitchen scissors.
Put in large mixing bowl. Pour half of pizza sauce, all of the pizza toppings and half the cheese in the bowl with biscuits. Toss until biscuits are evenly coated.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly with remaining sauce and cheese. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix together the pineapple, flour and sugar.
Mix together the Ritz crackers and butter.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: mexicana dip
directions: Spread out can of refried beans in casserole dish.
Heat slightly (3 minutes in microwave on High).
Add layer of sour cream.
Add layer of salsa.
Chop up black olives for next layer. Add layer of shredded cheese.
Grab a nacho chip and dig in!

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Beat in 6 remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan for 20 minutes a 375°.
While warm, spread icing on top.

title: abuelita's flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening finely.
Add water until you're able to handle.
Form dough and let it rest for 30 minutes.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Pat or roll to thin circle. Brown on each side in cast-iron skillet or griddle.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Dice up boiled egg. Mix all ingredients in saucepan and cook until hot.

title: elsie's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, flavoring and flour. Use only enough flour to handle dough.
Roll thin on pastry cloth; trim with slightly beaten egg whites and decorate with colored sugar and nuts if desired.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Cook rhubarb without water.
When cooked, add Jell-O, sugar and pineapple.
Mix well in bowl.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until jello consistency.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: *Boneless rump, top round, bottom round, arm blade, inside roll or shoulder roll.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and put cookies on cookie sheet.
Put in oven on 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crispy shrimp tempura batter
directions: Beat egg yolks with beer, oil, soy sauce and ginger for 2 minutes well.
Just before ready, beat egg whites until stiff. Fold egg whites into the rest of batter.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar and shortening.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Microwave onion in margarine for 2 minutes on High.
Add crabmeat, cheese, evaporated milk and flour.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Stir and turn bowl 1/2 turn; microwave 3 minutes on High.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Heat oil in cooker until paper match laying in oil on the bottom of the cooker bursts into flames.
Slowly lower breast into cooker and cook until outside is dark brown.
Unbelievably simple - unbelievably good!

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put into jars; add garlic and hot pepper. Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour into jars and seal.
Put in hot water bath for 5 minutes to seal.

title: southern barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper on ribs.
Put barbecue sauce, wine and garlic over ribs and cover.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Makes one nice full pie.
Make night before and have covered in refrigerator (is best).
Put in either the Easy Pie Crust or graham cracker crust. I like the Easy Pie Crust better.

title: florida orange meringue pie
directions: Combine juice, orange sections, rind, sugar and cornstarch over medium heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove and add small amount slowly to the 3 beaten egg yolks. Return to stove and cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat, add lemon juice and butter; let cool.
Pour in baked pie shell. Top with meringue; bake until done.
(Very Good!)

title: italian cream cake(my mother's)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk; let stand a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites; gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake in 4 greased, floured layer pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost cooled cakes with a double recipe of Cream Cheese Icing.
Makes 2 (2 layer) cakes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Melt margarine and mix well with other ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll at once in confectioners sugar and again when cool.

title: white bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Place milk, shortening, salt and sugar in large mixing bowl and wait until it is lukewarm.
Then add softened yeast mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add 4 cups sifted flour and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Cover with clean cloth and place in fairly warm place.
Let rise for about 30 minutes.
Then remove cloth, add remaining flour and mix well. Turn dough onto floured board and knead until satiny smooth, about 10 minutes.
Round dough into smooth ball and place in a larger bowl.
Cover with clean cloth and place in warm spot away from drafts.
Allow to rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch dough down and cut in half, then each portion half again.
Mold into loaves and place each loaf into greased bread pan.
Cover with a clean cloth and let loaves rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake loaves 1 hour at 375° for about 15 minutes at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn off and heat for the last 15 minutes.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and shape into 18 balls and brown on all sides in butter in skillet.
Remove meatballs and brown mushrooms lightly in drippings in skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons onion and blend in flour and steak sauce.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream and bring to boil.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Remove meatballs to a hot serving dish. Stir sour cream into liquid in skillet; add more seasoning if necessary and pour over meatballs.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's salsa
directions: Cut up scallions 1-inch size.
In blender, combine scallions, jalapenos, tomatoes and garlic salt.
Blend on medium speed for approximately 30 seconds or to desired chunkiness.
Salsa for dips can be chunky. Salsa for meals can be smoother. Cilantro can be added with all ingredients for a little different flavor. This salsa has a medium spicy flavor.

title: potato soup mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.

title: wassail(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Pour cider into lower part of 12-cup electric coffee maker. Place basket in coffee maker and put all remaining ingredients in basket. Cover and perk.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in large pan.
Bring to a boil and boil not more than one minute.
Add peanut butter, then add Rice Krispies. Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips together and frost mixture in pan.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Bring enough water to cover whole (unpeeled) squash to a boil. Boil squash 20-30 minutes until easily pierced with a fork. Remove squash from water and let sit until cool enough to handle. Cut squash lengthwise and scoop or scrape out seeds. Using a fork, scrape out strands of squash. Place squash in a well-greased casserole and dot with butter. Add salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle top with Romano. Before serving, heat squash about 12-15 minutes at 325 degrees. Stir before serving.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom with layer of graham crackers, then pudding mix, then graham crackers, then top with softened frosting. Chill 12 hours before serving.

title: aunt michele's famous apple butter
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat until thickened.
Should slide off spoon.
Takes a l-o-n-g time.
A crock-pot works well. Heat to boiling.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with a mixer.
Add eggs. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool overnight.

title: prune cake
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar and oil.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each.
Add the rest of the ingredients at one time.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in sheet cake pan.

title: citrus skillet chicken and rice(serves 4)
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, heat half the oil. Cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add remaining oil. Add rice and onion and cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth and orange juice.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until rice is done, stirring often.
Remove chicken to platter.
Stir parsley into rice mixture.
Garnish with orange slices before serving.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and salt.
Blend in syrup and gradually add milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat for 20 minutes, being sure not to let temperature get over 245° (use candy thermometer). Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Score before totally cooled.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples in baking pan, top with water and lemon juice.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: creamy herb dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese for 30 seconds.
Add chives, thyme, garlic powder and pepper.
Beat in enough milk (about 1/4 cup) to make the proper consistency.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese food with softened cream cheese, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mold into 1 or 2 small balls.
Chill until firm.
Roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook, wash and drain macaroni; cool.
Mix all ingredients together and pour evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle paprika on top and bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover bowl tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours, but no longer then 5 days.
Punch down dough.
Shape; let rise and bake at 400° until brown.

title: paella
directions: Saute shrimp and garlic in butter for about 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch; saute 1 minute.
Add broth, tomatoes, pepperoni, vegetables and pepper.
Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice and saffron.
Cover; remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mash salmon.
Stir in potatoes, water, mayonnaise and onion until blended.
Divide mixture into 8 portions and form into patties.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet until hot, but not smoking.
Fry patties in 2 batches 3 minutes per side until golden brown, adding more oil as needed.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gramma's elderberry pie
directions: Pour elderberries into pastry shell.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; sprinkle over berries, then lemon juice.
Cover with top crust, moistening edges to seal.
Cut gashes to allow steam to vent.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in airtight container. Use 1/3 cup dry mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: top hat pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sliced onion first, then a slice of lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon barbecue sauce.

title: pepper steak
directions: Dip steak in flour; saute in 1/2 cup butter for 2 minutes. Add rest of butter.
Saute separately, pepper, onions and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix together cornstarch, wine and soy sauce. Add to skillet.
Cook until thick; add meat.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread broccoli on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then put chicken over broccoli.
Add rice.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise together.
Pour over rice.
Add cheese and crackers.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beer batter for fish or deep fried vegetables
directions: Where the trees meet over the street,

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
(You can add or subtract ingredients to your own taste.)
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour until dark (very, very brown).
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Fry chicken, ham, sausage and shrimp.
Place in large pot, adding 2 quarts water or more if needed.
Cook until all is tender.
Add parsley, salt and pepper. Just before serving, add enough file to thicken and serve over cooked rice.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Mix puddings with milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Line large bowl with vanilla wafers.
Top with layer of bananas, then pudding.
Repeat layers until all is used.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cut onions fine; brown slightly with garlic in oil.
Add ground beef; brown.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook for 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.
Add other ingredients and heat thoroughly. Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Makes enough sauce for 2 pounds spaghetti.

title: cherry cinnamon jello(apple cinnamon jello)
directions: Over low heat dissolve candy in boiling water stirring constantly. Add jello and continue stirring until jello is dissolved. Cool slightly and add applesauce. Pour into 8 x 8 pan. Refrigerate.

title: crusty bread sticks
directions: Open and separate the biscuits.
Cut each biscuit in half. Roll each half between hands until 5 inches long.
Dip in the Pet milk (cream), then roll in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese or 1/4 cup poppy or caraway seed.
Spread thinly on waxed paper.
Place bread sticks on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden.
Makes 20.

title: 3 layer brownie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Spoon into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with marshmallows.
Cover with aluminum foil and let stand 5 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Spread Chocolate Frosting on top.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: garlic cashews
directions: Bake raw cashews on dry sheet at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden.
While baking, stir 2 or 3 times with wooden spoon.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream of chicken and cream of celery soup with celery.
Add stuffing crumbs and seasoning packet and water. Mix well and fold in chicken.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage ring
directions: Mix together and press into a well-oiled 12 cup ring mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Turn out into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 generously.

title: lamb shish-ka-bob
directions: Mix all ingredients overnight.
Place meat on skewers and grill.
Serve with Assyrian Rice.

title: creamy chicken cordon bleu(low-carb)
directions: Pound chicken breasts until fairly thin; saut in butter over medium heat to brown nicely. Place all 6 breasts in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top each piece of chicken with a slice of ham and then with a slice of the cheese.

title: irish stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Remove skin and fat.
Peel onions and chop one.
Wash and peel potatoes and cut in two.
Slice one thinly.
Place meat in bottom of stewpan, then put in the sliced potatoes and chopped onion, seasoned with pepper and salt.
Add water.
Boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Arrange the potatoes and onions on top and simmer for a further hour.
When cooked, serve on hot dish, meat in center of onions and potatoes.
Pour gravy over and garnish with parsley.

title: zesty potatoes
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes, but do not peel.
Spread potatoes in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with dry mix.
Slice margarine over dish and add water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Pour boiling water over the kidney beans and let them soak overnight.
The next day, drain the beans and place them in a large saucepan.
Fill with water to 3 inches above the beans. Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes, until just done.
Drain and set aside.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In 9 x 13 sprayed pan, combine everything except corn flakes. Mix well.
Top with corn flakes and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for the first 30 minutes, then uncover for final baking.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn country spoon bread
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sour cream, salt and cornbread mix in a bowl. Melt margarine in an 8 X 12 X 2 inch casserole dish.
Pour corn mixture over margarine.
Add peppers and onions.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine, sugar and honey.
Add egg substitute and beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in walnuts and pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 75 minutes.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Basic Equipment:
Wooden spoon, a large heavy pan with plenty of boiling space (about 8 inches).

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Set aside.
Using same beaters but different bowl, beat yolks until lemon colored.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat well.
Add hot water. Beat and then add other 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla. Beat well.
Slowly add dry ingredients until well blended.
Fold in whites carefully until no white shows.
Grease jelly roll pan and line with wax paper on bottom. Pour dough in pan and spread evenly.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Layer 1/2 cups sauce, zucchini, grated Mozzarella and slices of Cheddar.
Repeat.
Top with 1 1/2 cups sauce in greased casserole dish.
Cover and cook in microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn midway.

title: zippy beef-olive spread
directions: Soften cream cheese by leaving at room temperature an hour or so before using.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and serve with crackers.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add cold water to form dough. Place in container and cover.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Roll and cut out.
Place filling in half.
Fork over and press edges with fork.
Fry in hot shortening.

title: monterey chicken rice bake
directions: Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add and mix remaining ingredients except corn chips. Pour into shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked hash au gratin
directions: Mix thoroughly meat, potatoes, onion, salt, relish and ketchup. Add milk to blend together.
Spread 1-inch thick in a baking dish.
Sprinkle mixed cheese and crumbs over the top.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: squash muffins
directions: Mix together and bake in muffin tins at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Put salt over cabbage.
Mix.
Press down.
Let set 1 hour, then drain.
Boil sugar, vinegar and water for 3 minutes.
Cool, then mix with other ingredients.
Will keep 10 weeks in fridge.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies; save one cup for topping.
Mix remaining cookies with melted margarine and press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and 2 cups Cool Whip; put on top of cookies.
Mix 3 cups milk and pudding; spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle reserved cup of cookie crumbs on top.

title: potato halushkie
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Add milk and other ingredients and mix well
so that mixture makes a dough.
Cut off pieces of dough with a spoon and place into boiling water which has been slightly salted.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes until the dough rises to the top of the pot.
Strain and pour cold water over the halushkie.
Saute onion which has been diced and pour over halushkie.

title: monkey bread("a family favorite")
directions: Brush interior of the mold well with melted butter or spray with vegetable cooking spray.
Open biscuit tubes and separate. Dip them individually in the melted butter and layer in mold.
Be sure that each biscuit overlaps the last and that each new layer alternates with the one below it.
Arrange the last eight or nine biscuits in an overlapping circle around the top.
Place biscuit-filled mold on 8-inch round cake pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake an additional 30 minutes or until done (tap the top -- it will sound hollow).
Remove the bread from the mold onto a serving plate and serve hot.
It can be served bottom side up or inverted to show off the design, whichever looks best.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: peach and pineapple salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread dry Jell-O on cream cheese. Bring to a boil the sugar and crushed pineapple, then pour into jello mixture.
With hand mixer, beat at high speed until blended. Pour cold evaporated milk into a 2 1/2-quart bowl and whip until stiff, then fold into Jell-O mixture.
Mix with spoon until thoroughly mixed, then pour into 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chips in margarine, vanilla and Eagle Brand milk on low heat; combine marshmallows and nuts (any one of the nuts, your choices) in a large bowl.
Stir in chocolate mixture; spread in aluminum foil lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Keep at room temperature.

title: french pecans
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix pecans in and take out, one at a time.
Put on a buttered cool cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Cook pecans for 30 minutes. Turn oven off and leave in for 10 minutes.
Move from cookie sheet to waxed paper.
Will store in tin container only.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, juice and pudding together. Add remaining ingredients and chill for several hours.

title: raisin casserole bread(no kneading)
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar, salt and margarine and cool to lukewarm.
Measure water and spread yeast into it, then add to the milk mixture and 3 cups flour.
Beat well at this point.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a mixing bowl, about an hour or until double in bulk.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: real fudge cake
directions: In saucepan, combine 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup milk, beaten egg and chocolate.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts and mixture comes just to boiling.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, creaming together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Add remaining eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 cup milk, beginning and ending with flour and beating after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Bake in two paper lined round pans in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Frost and fill cooled layers with Chocolate Frosting.
Trim with curls of shaved unsweetened chocolate.

title: yellow sheet cake(birthday cake)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately to batter, with milk.
Bake in two 10-inch cake pans (greased and floured) or three 9-inch cake pans or aluminum sheet pan.
Bake at 365° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: dough for dried apple pies
directions: Mix oil, egg, buttermilk and flour and roll out into desired size.

title: cut out cookies
directions: Add all ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill about 2 hours or roll out at once.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove, cool, ice and decorate.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar and egg yolks. Sift together flour and soda; add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes three layers.

title: microwave cheese cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust by combining crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into 9-inch glass pie plate; set aside.
In glass bowl, melt the cream cheese on High in microwave for approximately 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix together the egg, 1/3 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Blend egg mixture into cream cheese.
Pour over crust.
Bake on High 1 minute; rotate plate and continue baking 1 more minute.
Cool 1 hour and serve.

title: pork with wine and herbs
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Season meat with salt and pepper; coat lightly with flour.
Brown meat on both sides in 1/4 cup butter. Cover; bake for 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven. Place a slice of cheese on each cutlet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Add remaining ingredients to pan, stirring to scrape up brown bits in the bottom.
Simmer and reduce sauce to about 3/4 cup.
Spoon over meat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork and corn stuffing
directions: Combine soup, stuffing, onion and paprika.
Spoon stuffing in 9-inch pie pan.
Arrange pork chops and press slightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard; spread lightly over pork chops.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Be sure pork chops are done.

title: governor's jambalaya
directions: Marinate shrimp in rum. Combine with water for 1 hour, turning occasionally. Saut onion in bacon drippings until lightly browned.
Add sausage (broken in pieces) and the shrimp with rum. Simmer gently 2 or 3 minutes. Transfer to heavy 3-quart pot. Add tomatoes, bay leaf, salt, pepper, thyme and rice.
Cover pot tightly and bring to a boil. Simmer gently for 20 minutes. Serve with freshly baked breadsticks or rolls.

title: jazzy beef bites
directions: Combine catsup, horseradish, mustard, onion, salt and dash of pepper.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Combine ground beef and bread crumbs.
Stir in catsup mixture. Shape meat around cheese into 3/4-inch balls. Cook in hot oil for about 1 1/2 minutes or until done.
Makes 30.

title: fruit delight
directions: Break up angel food cake; put aside.
