Combine cheese and Cool Whip, then lightly fold into angel food cake.
Put contents into a glass bowl, then drizzle pie filling over cake mixture.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup in small saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place 6 slices of bread on top of syrup mixture.
Top with remaining bread.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt; stir until blended.
Pour over bread and refrigerate, covered, for 9 hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil; add cream cheese and stir until melted. Dissolve gelatin in the 1/2 cup cold water and add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: guam fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and pour off half the bacon fat.
Fry garlic.
Remove and discard.
Fry onion in same fat.
Remove and add to bacon.
Spread eggs on bottom of pan as if preparing to make an omelet.
Remove to plate.
Add cold rice and stir until all grains are coated with grease and not sticking together.
Add bacon, onion and ham.
Mix well, always scraping bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Turn heat to low and add chopped egg pieces.
Add shrimp.
Remove from heat and serve. Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven.
Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef chowder
directions: In Dutch oven over medium heat, in hot salad oil.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add beef stew, undiluted celery soup and remaining ingredients and cook, covered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pear ambrosia
directions: Put pears and oranges, unpeeled, through food chopper.
Be sure to let all the juice go into container too.
Cook until pears are done.
Chop cherries.
Add all other ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.
Pour in hot jars; seal and water process 15 minutes at simmering temperature.
Makes 9 pints.

title: canine liver delight
directions: Blend liver in blender until mushy.
Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Place in lightly greased square pan (8 or 9-inch). Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
When cool, store in small freezer bags in freezer until ready to use.
Great training treats.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan. Stir in egg yolks, milk and water. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat. Add vanilla.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: One stick margarine may be substituted for one stick butter.

title: hummus
directions: Cook chickpeas in lightly salted water. Drain. Reserve liquid. Cool.
Peel chickpeas (this can be done by rolling peas between palms of hands to loosen skins).
Process in small amounts in food processor.
Process garlic.
Add tahini; mix well.
Add lemon or lime juice and as much cooking broth to make a medium thick dipping paste.
Place in dish with well in center. Top with olive oil, paprika or pepper and parsley. Serve with pita bread for dipping.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.
In separate bowl mix white sugar, brown sugar, oil, butter/margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 - 15 minutes until light brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp and drain well.
Place cream cheese on serving tray.
Place shrimp over cream cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce over all.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: pearlie's cherry crisp
directions: Spray pan real good.
Then mix butter, Rice Krispies, cheese, crumbs and sugar thoroughly.
Use half of it to press inside pan. Pour can of pie mix over this and then top with remaining mixture. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: meringue bunnies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar on medium speed until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating on high until stiff peaks form. Transfer to a pastry or plastic bag. On parchment lined baking sheets, pipe the meringue into 4 3/4-inch bunny shapes. Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours or until firm. Remove to wire racks.

title: wassail
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large pan.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Strain to remove cloves and cinnamon, add sugar and apple cider.
Simmer until heated through.
Serve hot.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute until pale golden.
Stir in all the remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes or until heated and flavors are blended.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: walnut butter cookies
directions: Into medium bowl sift flour, sugar and salt and add coffee. Cut in margarine until size of pea.
Press dough together.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in chopped walnuts and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 20 minutes until lightly browned in 350° oven.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger with onion, then add the other ingredients into a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes. Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In a 2-quart dish, mix broccoli and uncooked rice.
Mix other ingredients in separate bowl and pour over broccoli-rice.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, cool, peel and shred with coarse grater. Melt butter.
Add
sour
cream,
soup
and
cheese.
Stir over medium heat
until cheese melts.
Add onions and salt.
Spread 1/2 potatoes in an 8 x 13-inch pan, 1/2 cheese in layers.
Top with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix well and freeze.
At serving time, fill glass half full with slush and fill rest of way with 7-Up.

title: broccoli and cheese soupgroves, texas
directions: Melt butter in pan and saute broccoli and onions in butter for 3 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In a deep heavy skillet, melt oleo and stir in unbroken pecan halves.
Cook nuts	over
low heat, stirring frequently, for about 20 minutes	until lightly brown.
Sift confectioners sugar and spices.
Remove nuts from skillet with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Add	nuts to spiced sugar and toss until generously coated.
Turn
nuts
into
colander and shake gently to remove excess sugar.
Spread
nuts on paper towel to cool.
Store in lightly covered container.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken in spices at least 8 hours.
Broil on grill, brushing with extra sauce.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large frypan over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onions in butter until mushrooms are lightly browned, 6 to 8 minutes.
Arrange mushroom mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle Swiss cheese over mushroom mixture.
Beat together the eggs and remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over mushroom-cheese mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over ice.

title: o-so-good raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients except raisins.
Beat until smooth.
Add raisins; stir.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato-mac salad
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Boil eggs until hard-boiled and chop.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Mix ingredients; chill and serve.

title: alabama pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly.
Add 2 eggs at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour and beat.
Add flavorings and pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Needed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together in a large bowl pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, pudding, and graham crackers. Top with topping.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let spinach thaw.
Squeeze until dry.
Mix together other ingredients.
Slice long loaf of Italian bread and fill with spinach dip or take a purple cabbage and fill with spinach dip.

title: banana mousse
directions: Combine mashed banana, juices and sugar.
Mix well.
With an electric mixer, beat egg white until stiff.
Beat heavy cream until stiff and peaked.
Fold egg white into whipped cream.
Add banana mixture to cream mixture, blending well.
Pour into a freezer tray or 5-cup freezer containers or mold.
Cover; freeze 6 hours. Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Add cold water and mix well.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll out on floured waxed paper.
Will make 2 crusts.

title: crumb cake(crowd size)
directions: Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 16-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: best cake
directions: Mix; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add Ro-Tel, beans, chili and cheese. Heat until all is melted.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Lay steamed broccoli in bottom of large casserole dish.
Put chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
In large bowl, mix 2 cans soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pimiento, drained mushrooms and sauteed celery.
Pour and spread over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle on grated cheese, then buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients and then add liquid ones on medium-hot griddle.

title: frozen hot fudge delite
directions: Take ice cream out of freezer before you start.

title: italian butter
directions: Mix.
Use with crusty breads, baked chicken, zucchini, pasta.

title: chinese beef and pea pods
directions: Marinate steak for 1 hour in the next 4 ingredients.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in frying pan; add meat and brown lightly. Remove.
Add 2 more tablespoons oil, onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cook 2 minutes, tossing constantly.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, salt,
1/4 cup
soy sauce and garlic. Simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Blend 1 tablespoon cornstarch with sugar, 1 teaspoon soy sauce, Accent and 1 cup chicken broth. Cook until thickens.
Add meat and pea pods.
Just heat through, don't overcook.
Serve with rice.

title: maple syrup
directions: Cook about 10 minutes or until it starts to thicken a little. Let cool before serving.

title: hazelnut toffee
directions: Line large baking sheet with foil. Sprinkle 1/2 cup hazelnuts onto 8-inch square in middle. Set aside. Butter sides of heavy 1-quart saucepan. Melt rest of butter. Add brown sugar and water. Stir over medium heat to boiling and cook to soft-crack stage (280°). Remove pan from heat. Stir in liqueur and pour over nuts in pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and let stand 2 minutes. When chocolate is soft, spread to cover, then sprinkle with remaining nuts. Cool. Lift candy from pan and break into pieces. Store in airtight container up to 2 weeks.

title: chocolate layered goodie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (flour, butter and pecans).
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and press the flour mixture into it.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Next, mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; spread over baked crust.
Next mix the pudding and milk.
Layer it on top of last mixture and decorate top with pecan pieces.
Keep chilled.

title: mincemeat pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Peel, core and chop into small pieces both pears and apples. Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Cook 45 minutes or until thickened.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush Oreos, save 1/4 cup for garnish.
Mix with melted butter.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.

title: rodenburger
directions: First you brown the ground beef, then you drain.
Next, you combine beans with the ground beef, ketchup and the mustard in a 3-quart saucepan.
Last, you simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: sarah's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar to eggs; continue to beat until sugar and eggs are well blended.
Heat milk mixture in saucepan over open heat.
When the milk is warm, pour in egg and sugar mixture.
Keep heat on low and constantly stir mixture so that it won't stick to bottom of saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and freeze in 2-gallon freezer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk together until thick, approximately 3 minutes.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer pudding with vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Slice the sausage in large pan.
Cook sausage, onion and pepper until tender.
Add soup mix, rice and water.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: miss belle's grape juice pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and grape juice until thick.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
When cool, top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: spanish-style steak
directions: Take round steak and season both sides with garlic.
Rub in well.
Sprinkle with rest of ingredients.
Put into frying pan. Add vinegar, oil and water.
Cut onion and green pepper; place on top of steak.
Cover.
Cook over low heat until well done and tender.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Mix in remaining ingredients (except cherries).
Freeze in sheet cake pan.
Place cherries on top.
Slice and serve.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth in a blender or food processor.
Wash and wilt spinach, then squeeze dry.
Add to mixture and blend to chop spinach.
Bake in a sprayed loaf pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned. This is not a high rise souffle.
Do not expect it to puff up too much.
To serve, allow to cool slightly, then turn out onto serving plate and slice.
Keeps well for days in refrigerator.

title: glorified onions
directions: Slice onions and soak overnight in the vinegar and sugar and water. Drain well and toss with mayo and celery salt. Serve on crackers or as a salad or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: sugar balls
directions: Cream margarine and granulated sugar.
Add flour and salt sifted together.
Add vanilla and stir in pecans.
Roll into balls and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight. Mix about 1/4 cup of sugar with red food coloring to make a red sugar crystal mix. Roll into balls and shape in strawberry size. Roll berry shape in sugar mix until lightly coated. Mix almond slivers with green food coloring and shake until the almond crystals are green. Stick slivers into the strawberry. Makes about 4 to 6 dozen.

title: canned green tomatoes for frying
directions: Pack tomatoes that have been sliced thick in large mouth jars. Fill with cold water and seal.
Place jars in canner (not pressure).
When it starts to boil, boil 5 minutes and no longer. Store in cool place. Drain well when ready to fry.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy skillet.
Drain and set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth and well blended.

title: kyle's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak in ice water to cover with salt for at least 3 hours.
Scald vinegar; add sugar and seasonings.
Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Just heat through. Put in sterilized jars, covering with vinegar solution, and seal.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in 1 cup of the rocks.
Spoon mixture into pie crust and sprinkle with remaining rocks.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with chocolate shavings, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Thaw roast if frozen.
Let roast stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Rub roast with vinegar.
Season with salt, pepper and fresh garlic.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place roast, rib side down, on a rack in baking pan.
Roast for 1 hour.
Allow roast to remain in oven all day.
Do not open door!
One hour before serving, turn oven back on to 375° and reheat roast.
Do not remove roast from oven or open door until ready to serve.
For well done roast, cook 15 to 30 minutes longer before serving.

title: grandmommie's chocolate dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix
cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 4 1/2 ounces Cool Whip. Spread on crust that has been cooled.
Mix 2 small boxes pudding with 3 cups milk.
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: raisin caraway soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add caraway seed.
Mix together.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add golden raisins.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine egg and buttermilk.
Add baking soda to sweeten.
It will bubble a bit. Quickly stir milk into dry ingredients.
Turn out on floured board and knead 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Form flat circle 1 1/2 inches high.
Place on greased baking sheet.
With floured knife, cut deep cross almost side to side.
Brush with beaten egg yolk. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Crust should sound hollow when tapped.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and chill.
Make small balls.
Pierce top with fork tines. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar after it cools slightly.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Heat butter and Karo syrup in skillet.
Add pecan halves. Stir until well coated.
Put into 325° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Pour out onto a split brown paper bag. Separate with fork.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Let cool, ready to serve.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 3-quart saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil
and
cook
minutes.
Drain
well.
While potatoes are draining,
make cheese sauce.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine;
slowly
stir
in
flour.
Gradually
add milk, stirring constantly.
Drop
cheese cubes in and continue to cook and
stir
until
cheese is completely melted.
Remove from heat and add
pimento
and
green onion tops.
In a large casserole, add potatoes.
Stir in cheese sauce and serve while hot.
Adjust milk for a thicker or thinner sauce.

title: basic sushi rice
directions: Wash rice. Drain and then add the water.
Let rice soak for 30 minutes. Cook in a rice cooker. When rice is done, let cool 15 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and cream with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Add pecans, raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies roughly with rolling pin.
Mix with melted butter until crumbs are coated.
Press 2/3 of crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze about 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Add powdered sugar and eggs.
Mix over low heat until fudgy.
Spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle pecans over fudge.
Slice ice cream and lay on top.
Sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Freeze at least 2 hours.

title: icing with style
directions: Blend cream cheese, dates and walnuts.
Thin with milk to proper consistency.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; divide and spread evenly over pie shells.
Sprinkle half of walnuts over cream cheese; layer sliced strawberries and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining walnuts.
Serve chilled.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare dressing.
Place in a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top the dressing with chopped chicken.
Add cream soups on top of chicken.
Place foil on top or a lid and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until dressing is done.
(Freezes well up to 4 weeks.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour, stirring well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring well.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and cream together.
Add 3 cups chopped pecans, place on cookie sheet and chill.
Melt wax and chocolate chips; pour over candy.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove 1/2 cup cookie dough for later use.
Mix flour with remaining cookie dough.
Put on pan, making 14-inch round.
Bake for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Loosen from pan; let cool completely.
Blend the cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Peel and slice apples thin.
Dip apples in lemon-lime soda and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat caramel topping; spread on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top of topping.
Very delicious!

title: butterscotch bubble ring
directions: Thaw bread; quarter loaf lengthwise.
Cut each quarter into 8 pieces.
Combine pudding mix, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Dip each cube in melted butter, then roll in pudding mix.
Place in a well-greased 12 cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle extra pudding mix between the layers.
Use up all pudding mix and melted butter before putting coffee cake in a warm place to rise.
Cover; allow to rise until double in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to stand for 2 minutes. Invert on a platter.
Yield:
10 servings.
Preparation time is 2 1/2 hours.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; add salt, sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Crumble or sprinkle yeast into warm water in large mixing bowl; stir to dissolve yeast.
Add 1/3 of flour and beat until smooth. Add remaining flour and gradually to make a soft dough which leaves the sides of bowl.
Turn out dough onto floured board.
With floured hands, knead dough until it is smooth and elastic, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin puffs
directions: In saucepan boil water; add raisins.
Boil until water is gone. Cool.
Combine flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat together sugar and margarine until combined.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until blended. Stir in raisins.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls; roll in cinnamon sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 70.

title: tummy bars
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup milk in bowl.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips and nuts over baked bottom layer. Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread rest of cake mix over the caramel layer.
Bake for 20 more minutes.

title: low-fat corn muffins
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the honey, eggs, egg whites, milk and oil.
Add the dry ingredients and mix with an electric mixer at medium-high speed for 2 minutes.
Spray 2 muffin tins with cooking spray or line with baking cups.
Fill each cup 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until tops are golden brown.
Makes 24, 155 calories and 3 grams fat.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss lettuce, tomato, onion and cheese.
Brown beef and add beans.
Mix in chips and dressing.
Can save 1 cup chips to put on top.

title: carrots
directions: Cut up carrots.
Cook in salted water until a little bit tender.
Drain.
Boil together remaining ingredients except onions and green pepper.
Pour over carrots, onions and green peppers.

title: carrots in orange sauce
directions: Peel and cut carrots in half lengthwise.
Place in heavy saucepan with water, lemon juice, salt and butter.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Blend cornstarch, orange juice and honey. Drain fluid from carrots and add orange juice mixture to the liquid and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over carrots and sprinkle with chives.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; toss together.

title: seasoned salt
directions: To make saltless seasoning salt, combine:

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper and flour.
Cook until red is gone from ground beef, about 10 minutes.
Add soup and mushrooms; cook for 5 minutes. Add sour cream and remove from heat.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef with 1/2 package taco seasoning. Drain very well. Set aside.

title: feta-tomato crostini
directions: Brush cut side of each roll with olive oil.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil 6 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Place cheese evenly on each roll.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder. Place tomatoes over cheese.
Drizzle with balsamic vinegar and sprinkle with mint.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash berries with sugar
and let stand 30 minutes.
Mix with cornstarch and cook
until	thick
and
clear.
Pour over berries and refrigerate.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix margarine, pretzels and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries.
Set in refrigerator until soupy. Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
When crust is cool, spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Then pour jello mixture over the top.
Let set in refrigerator until completely set up.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 c. warm water.
Melt shortening, sugar and salt in 3/4 c. warm water.
Add egg, also the dissolved yeast to the above mixture.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Let stand in warm place until twice in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down and add flour until you can roll.
Make in desired shape.
Let rise until twice in size about 1 hour.
Brush with butter and bake in 400 degree oven about 6 minutes for brown and serve rolls.
Bake longer if you plan to eat them immediately.
These rolls are fine for reheating.

title: caramel topping(diabetic recipe)
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil. Swirl mixture (do not stir) until clear.
Cover pan tightly; boil over moderately high heat for about 10 minutes, swirling constantly.
Remove cover; continue boiling while swirling until syrup turns light brown.
Remove from heat; allow syrup to cool as you heat evaporated milk.
Add heated milk to syrup, stirring constantly.
Simmer until syrup dissolves in milk.
Add extracts. Continue simmering to thicken slightly.
Serve warm or cold.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let batter stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: egg bake(zesti-egg strata)
directions: Lightly saute or cook sausage or other meat.
Mix together bread cubes, sausage, celery, onions, green pepper and cheese in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish (Pyrex works best).
Combine eggs, milk, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over mixture. Spread undiluted soup over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain ground chuck.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook and simmer 1 hour.
Place cottage cheese and eggs in blender until smooth.
Stir in salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Drain.
Use 2 baking dishes.
Layer meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat, ending with meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand about 15 minutes.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine the contents of the potato package, corn, tomatoes and water; mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, cheese and hot pepper sauce; cook and stir until cheese is melted. Garnish with sprinkle of parsley if desired.

title: crab omelette
directions: Halve tomatoes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, butter and basil. Broil for 4 minutes. Remove and top with grated Parmesan cheese. Broil until browned.
Serve as a side dish with any meat.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Place margarine in a deep-dish pie plate and set in the 350° oven until margarine is melted.

title: snow on the mountain
directions: Brown meat until cooked and crumbly.
Drain off excess fat. Place in bottom of greased casserole.
Cover with catsup, corn and then peas.
Top with a generous frosting of mashed potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for about an hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top for last 15 minutes of cooking, if desired.

title: no bake strawberry bottom cheese cake
directions: Slice strawberries.
Put on a paper towel to drain.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spread thin layer of glaze over bottom of crust.
Place strawberry slices on glaze and cover with another thin layer of glaze. Gently spoon mixture over glazed berries in crust.
Cover with inverted dome and chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: piquant cocktail meatballs
directions: *Use ground round so there isn't a lot of fat floating in pan.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in flavorings.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cake flour, mixing well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.
Yields 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: chef's salad
directions: In large salad bowl, tear lettuce into bite size pieces. Reserve some of the meat and cheese strips.
Toss remaining strips with onion, bell pepper, celery, carrots and bacon bits.
Pour favorite salad dressing over salad and toss.
Garnish with saved meat and cheese strips, egg slices and tomatoes.

title: barbecue in a biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger in a skillet and drain. Spray muffin pan and press biscuits in to form cups of dough.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce to hamburger; stir well.
Spoon hamburger mixture into biscuits.
Cook 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Remove from oven.
Add cheese.
Turn off oven and replace biscuits to melt cheese.
Serve.

title: friendship cake
directions: Set your heart at warm temperature; mix ingredients smoothly with complete faith in God. Scrape bowl thoroughly, because great joy of life is to be found at bottom. Spread with tenderness and sprinkle with sympathy and kindness. Cut in generous slices. More goodness is found underneath than is shown on surface. Serve with a smile and hospitality in a large dish of compassion. Offer it to your neighbors. Yields enough for everyone.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; cool slightly.
Pull off bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with chicken pieces.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine in pot the brown sugar, salt and cider.
Tie allspice, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg in small piece of cheesecloth.
Slowly bring mixture of brown sugar, salt and cider to boil, with tied spices in the pot.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove the spices.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream margarine and both sugars; add eggs, then the rest of ingredients.
Bake in cake pan 9 x 13-inch at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
These should not be overbaked or they will not be moist.

title: megan's bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan, put rolls in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding, sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Spread nuts over everything.
Pour butter over top.
Leave on countertop overnight; do not cover.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: The next time you make white sauce, make a "big batch" of it, thick.
Drop one tablespoon at a time on a cookie sheet leaving a little space between.
Put the sheet in the freezer and when frozen put into plastic bags.
The next time you want to cream peas, etc., take out the required number of chips and thaw in saucepan or microwave.
Thin with milk to desired consistency.

title: bacon and egg pie
directions: Beat eggs; add salt and pepper, nutmeg and milk.
Put bacon and cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Add egg mixture and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, cook brown sugar, margarine and milk until large bubbles form and burst.
Stir frequently. Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar until creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix 1/3 cup evaporated milk, margarine and cake mix.
Spread 1/2 cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 6 minutes.
Pour on caramel.
Sprinkle nuts.
Drop rest of cake batter on by teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: mock mini cheesecake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla until sugar is blended in
and mixture loses its grainy feel.
Put small amount of cream mixture on flat side of vanilla wafer.
Top with single cherry.
Keep in fridge until time to serve.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Saute hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add seasonings and pizza sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Spread on a split English muffin and top with Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: aunt thom's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks.
Mix all.
Add flour, milk and vanilla alternately.
After all mixed, fold in egg whites. Butter and flour tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: picante-dijon grilled chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/2-inch thickness; set aside. Combine picante sauce, mustard and sugar; mix well.
Place chicken over medium-hot coals; brush generously with sauce.
Grill about 6 to 8 minutes per side or until chicken is tender and no longer pink, brushing occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
After the ingredients are brought to a boil, add oatmeal mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
When cool, they are ready to eat.
Makes about 18 to 20.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, oil and egg.
Pare and slice apples and place in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well. Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: golden chicken and rice
directions: Heat soup and cheese over low heat until melted.
Add rice, onion and pimiento; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Put chicken on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 more minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the yellow cake mix over the top.
Slice the margarine on top of the cake mix.
Sprinkle the nuts on top of the margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the cake feels done to the touch.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables in a saucepan with 1 cup of water.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento, water chestnuts and 1/2 can French fried onion rings. Cook, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; add remaining cheese and onion.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs, flour, sugar, milk, vanilla and margarine together.
Pour into pie plate and bake in a moderate oven 30 minutes at 325° until firm.

title: peachy macaroon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain peaches and set aside.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy; beat in egg and extract.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Spread dough into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Arrange peach slices on top of dough; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Dip chicken in wash and bread with breadcrumbs.
Fry quickly until golden brown.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix with the margarine, honey and mustard together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes covered with foil.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Saute onions in bacon grease. Drain.
Cover potatoes in water and cook until just done.
Add bacon, onions, corn and milk.
Simmer slowly on low heat, stirring frequently to avoid sticking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted oleo; set aside. Mix all other ingredients and 1/2 of stuffing mixture. Pour into buttered casserole dish (can use fat-free cooking spray). Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: blackberry shrub
directions: Combine blackberry juice and sugar until dissolved.
Combine lemonade and ginger ale; add to fruit liquid.
Serve on crushed ice.

title: trifle
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
In a clear, glass bowl, put half the cake pieces in bottom.
Add half the cherry filling, mixed with the Amaretto, over cake.
Make pudding according to package directions and spread half over cherries.
Next, add half of the Cool Whip, covering the pudding.
Repeat next layers the same.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut squash in circular slices.
Cut broccoli flowerets to desired size.
String snow pea pods.
In a wok or large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat about 3 minutes. Turn heat to high.
Add snow pea pods.
Cook about 3 minutes. Stir constantly.
Add squash.
Cook until tender, not mushy. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash Table Blend and low sodium soy sauce over vegetables to taste.
Add bean sprouts.
Reduce heat to low. Cover.
Cook about 2 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together in a large glass bowl. Spray a light coat of vegetable spray over the bottom of a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Add the chicken mixture. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes to an hour.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Place marshmallow cream in a bowl.

Place the sugar, salt and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil (soft ball stage, 234°). Pour syrup mixture over marshmallow cream and stir with mixer until slightly stiff peaks form. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan or drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spray a square pan with Pam.
Pour cherry pie filling in. Combine melted oleo, cake mix and pecans until well mixed (almost like dough).
Crumble mixture on top of cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 9.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Lightly grease 20 muffin cups.
Combine Mozzarella, Ricotta and Parmesan cheese until well mixed.
Pull apart or cut each biscuit in half horizontally.
Pat each half into muffin cup, forming a shell.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins, walnut and vanilla.
Turn into two greased and lightly floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake on lowest rack at 350° for about 55 minutes until loaves test done.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire racks until cool.
This bread freezes well.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt together.
Then add these to sugar and oil mixture.
Next, add vanilla, apples, nuts and coconut.
The batter will be thick and easier to mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube or loaf pan.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Bake at 325° in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread and cube.
Set aside.
Place remaining bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix bread cubes with onion, celery, green pepper, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and chicken. Pour over bread slices in dish.
Mix eggs, milk and soup together, then pour over chicken mixture.
Chill about 1 hour. Sprinkle with cheese over soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven. Leftover turkey can be substituted for chicken.

title: miracle whip devil's food cake
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and Miracle Whip.
In sifter, combine flour, soda and salt; sift twice.
Add flour mixture to cocoa mixture alternately with water.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured layer pans or one oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce in pieces and spread in a round glass bowl.
Start layering vegetables.
I sometimes chopped tomatoes for color as one layer.
Layer in order given.
Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar and spread on top of salad.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble over mayonnaise.
Add cheese as next layer.
You can experiment with different vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate.

title: vegetable egg rolls
directions: In
a
bowl,
combine
soy
sauce, salt, cornstarch and sesame oil.
Set
aside.
Heat
a	wok or wide frying pan over high heat. When pan is hot, add salad oil.
When it begins to heat,
add ginger
and
stir.	Add
beans sprouts, mushrooms, celery and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry 2 minutes and add green onions.	 Stir in	soy
sauce-cornstarch
mixture	and
cook, stirring until liquid in pan thickens.
Cool.
Brush edges of wrapper with lightly beaten egg, after filling center with the vegetable mixture.
Roll
and fold into elongated shape.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Remove and drain excess oil.

title: raspberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
While hot, add raspberries, then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate and serve.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: marble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocoa and food coloring together. Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Add red food coloring to one part and cocoa to another part.
The third part remains vanilla.
Layer each color twice in tube pan.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: butter pecan crisp
directions: Pineapple may be substituted.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Pour in fruit with juice.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit. Slice oleo in thin slices over the top of dry mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: egg fried rice
directions: Put rice in large bowl.
Break eggs onto rice and add next 2 ingredients and 1 tablespoon minced onion.
Mix thoroughly with spoon, breaking up lumps.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Add rice mixture and stir over heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with green onions.

title: hettie pruitt's congealed fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice drained from canned fruit.
Add fruit and celery.
Pour into mold.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: strawberry figs
directions: One morning prayer, said gracefully,

title: uncooked spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Blend to desired consistency.
You may add more olive oil to thicken.
Pour over hot spaghetti and serve with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cook over medium/low heat 2 to 3 hours.
(Cook long enough to be sure chicken is cooked through).
Serve over tortilla strips. Garnish with avocado and Cheddar cheese.

title: best ever chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add the beans and rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: buttery cream cake
directions: Melt margarine. Mix together with cake mix and 1 egg. Put into bottom of 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: meatloaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place bread in the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade; pulse until fine crumbs form. Transfer to a medium bowl, and add ground beef.
Place onion, garlic, celery, carrots, and parsley in the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade; pulse until fine.
Add to meat mixture, using hands to mix well.
Add egg, 1/2 c. ketchup, 2 tsp. dry mustard, salt and pepper; use hands to combine thoroughly.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inch loaf pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, onion and celery with water.
Cook 10 minutes. Turn heat to simmer and add chicken broth, pimentos, parsley and milk to thickness as you want.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crackers.
Spoon onto waxed paper and cool.

title: celery casserole
directions: Slice and steam celery in small amount of water for 5 minutes. Mix soup, pimento and water chestnuts.
Add celery (drained) and blend.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs, blended with butter and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Bake in bread pan at 350° for one hour.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash covered in water for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Mash enough squash to measure 1 cup.
Combine squash and egg; stir well. Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion; stir until blended.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown (turn over once).
Drain well on paper towel.

title: creamed corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into hot, well-greased skillet. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In small 6-inch iron skillet, add the oil and heat. Mix together all other ingredients. Add the heated oil and pour into the heated skillet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in oven until brown.

title: sweet nothings(microwave)
directions: Melt
margarine,
chips and peanut butter in microwave. Mix well.
Pour
Rice
Chex
into
melted mixture and stir to coat. Pour
powdered
sugar into grocery sack.
Add Rice Chex mixture in sack and shake.
Store in airtight container.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Don't drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and alum. Heat.
Bring to boil.
Let cool, then pour on cucumbers.
Put in airtight bowl or container and put in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time.

title: almond butter sauce
directions: Saute the almonds slowly in 2 tablespoons of butter until golden brown. Cool.
Cream the remaining butter and the almonds, pimiento, parsley, lemon juice and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve with fried or broiled seafood.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
This also works good if you bake it in an iron skillet.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain off grease. Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and Mozzarella cheese together.
Spoon over hamburger mixture.
Unroll crescent rolls. Divide into 2 rectangular halves and lay on top of cheese mixture. Pour melted margarine over rolls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare three 9-inch cake pans.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together, then mix in a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add grated carrots and crushed pineapple.
Put batter into the three cake pans and bake for 30 to 40 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool layers.
While baking and cooling, make the frosting.
Then stack layers with it.
For an extra touch, grated nuts can be sprinkled between layers and on top.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients together in bowl. Pour into a casserole dish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream the butter and sugar. Stir in flour and oatmeal. Form 1-inch balls and place onto ungreased cookie sheet. Mash each cookie with floured fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoonfuls in a greased muffin pan, filling 1/2 to 3/4 full.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Fry meat; add taco seasoning and refried beans.
Mix well. Spoon this filling into shells and roll up.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Spoon small amount of this mixture in/on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay filled shells, seam side down, in pan.
Spoon and spread remaining soup/sour cream mixture over filled shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbly.
May drizzle taco sauce over top, if desired.
Serve with chopped vegetables listed above and with salsa.
One package of 10 burrito shells makes two 13 x 9-inch pans full.

title: baked chicken with vegetables(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken breast on large piece of foil; add vegetables, seasoning and salad dressing.
Wrap and bake for 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, cream, milk and butter and cook slowly to form ball at 248°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and then put on a board and cut into squares; wrap in wax paper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown hash browns and sausage.
In 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, spread crescent rolls.
Put sausage over crescent roll dough.
Next put hash browns over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over hash browns. Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll in bite size balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tipsy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Put in pan and let simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in pita bread. Serves 2 for lunch.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top with a little sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: back-bay salad
directions: Use a large flat dish and layer (in order listed): lettuce, frozen peas, sliced onions and mayonnaise (spread over top). Cover and refrigerate overnight, then continue layering before serving: olives, bacon and tomatoes.

title: candied pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place aluminum foil on a cookie sheet and add pecans. Mix brown sugar and orange juice and drizzle over pecans. Bake 6 minutes, stir and bake 6 minutes more. Pour on a piece of aluminum foil and drizzle any liquid on top. Separate into singles or clusters after cool.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in large saucepan and cover with water; cook until tender but firm.
Drain.
Cut potatoes in 1 inch cubes. Place in an ungreased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add pimentos, onion, garlic salt and onion salt; toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place bread cubes on top and pour butter over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: creamy pudding
directions: Heat 4 cups of milk.
Beat eggs; add sugar and 1/2 cup milk. Add flour and cornstarch.
Slowly add 1/2 cup milk to heated milk. Stir constantly.
Cool very good and add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Beat very good.
Delicious with cake and pies.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet; chill 2 more hours.
Dip balls into 2 eggs and 1/4 cup milk, mixed.
Roll balls in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then deep fry.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine with pastry blender.
Beat eggs, then beat them into the sugar mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients. Mix together applesauce and corn syrup.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture alternately.
Add to batter the 1 cup raisins.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and Karo; add rest.
Pour in pie shell and bake for about an hour or until pie shows cracks in a 325° oven.

title: borsch
directions: Cook beef shank down. Discard bone; dice meat. Add beets, cabbage, onion, carrots, potatoes, dill and garlic. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cover with fried bacon strips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pour into crust. Must freeze overnight. Cut into 8 pieces. Serves 8.

title: microwave cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in 3-quart microwave casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until boiling.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: mocha swirl cheesecake
directions: Grease spring-form pan.
Press nuts onto the bottom and 2 inches up the side.
Set aside.
Heat chocolate, water and 1 teaspoon coffee crystals in a pan over low heat until melted. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, flour and vanilla with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat on low until combined.
Remove 1/3 of batter, stir in cool chocolate mixture. Stir the milk and dissolved coffee into remaining batter.
Pour 1/2 of light batter into spring-form pan.
Spoon 1/2 of chocolate batter over top.
Repeat.
Make a few swirls using knife.
Bake on a shallow pan in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until center appears nearly set.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Loosen crust from pan with knife.
Cool 30 minutes more.
Remove sides.
Cool.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in refrigerator 1 or 2 hours before serving.
Good with wheat thins.

title: two step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar. Then add cool whip and beat till smooth. Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with favorite pie filling or other topping.

title: french toast silver lake style
directions: Wish Sandwich: Two pieces of bread and wish you had something to go on it.

title: tangy fruit dip
directions: Mix Tang with Cool Whip to taste. Add ginger ale until smooth (use more, if needed).

title: light chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour into hot crust and bake 30 minutes.
Top is not too brown.
Put under broiler for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Put powdered sugar on top; cut into squares.

title: last minute stroganoff
directions: Brown the ground beef in 10-inch skillet.
Add chopped onions. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add hot water, mushroom pieces, catsup, scalloped potatoes and sauce mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add the sour cream just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cool and creamy fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.
This keeps well in refrigerator.

title: egg flower soup
directions: Boil the broth.
Add cornstarch, sugar, salt and soy sauce. Pour in the eggs in a slow stream.
Stir slowly and they will separate into shreds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: roasted halibut with woodland mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On top of the stove, melt the butter in a baking dish.
Dip the fish into the butter to coat it on both sides.
Spread top and bottom of the fish with mustard.
Dredge both sides of fish in bread crumbs combined with chopped parsley. Season with salt and pepper.
Bake the fish at 350° for 20 minutes or until white all the way through.

title: scottsdale potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 7 x 10-inch glass baking dish. Combine first 6 ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put into dish; mix cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted butter. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate, top with chilies.
Beat milk, mix and eggs until smooth. Pour in plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.

title: kettle corn
directions: Spray whirlybird popper pan, stirrer, and inside lid with PAM. Put oil, sugar, & corn into popper and turn heat on high.
Stir constantly.
When popping SLOWS (NOT STOPS!), remove from heat and empty into a large bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Stir or shake to distribute salt.
As popcorn cools, break apart with hands or a spoon if it's too hot.
Popcorn may be colored by adding a few drops of food coloring with the rest of the ingredients before popping.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix in bowl the sugar, flour and salt. Mix in saucepan the water, shortening, oleo and cocoa. Bring water mixture to a boil; pour over flour and sugar and stir well. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Pour in 8 x 11-inch pan and bake in 350° oven until done, approximately 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done. Cool and chop in food processor. Mix in other ingredients and add enough mayonnaise to mix.

title: michael's "foot stompin" chili
directions: Fry bacon strips and set aside.
In bacon grease, fry onions and garlic until translucent.
Strain onions and garlic and get rid of bacon grease.
Fry pork in Crisco, then strain, saving Crisco.
Fry round steak strips in (pork) Crisco.
Drain steak and put pork and steak into large kettle.
Fry ground beef with onions and garlic.
Drain off grease and put beef into kettle with other meats.
Add water, tomato paste and crushed fried bacon.
Cook on medium heat.

title: fruit tart
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder.
Drop in shortening and mix like pie crust.
Add egg yolks to milk and beat.
Add to flour mixture.
Use 1/2 for top crust and 1/2 for bottom crust.
Roll top out between wax paper to size of cookie sheet.
Put in freezer until you do bottom crust.
Put dough in cookie sheet and pat until cookie sheet is covered.
Add pie filling, then cover with top crust.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake until brown and bubbly at 375° (45 minutes).

title: kim brown's crunchy beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour half mixture in 2-quart greased casserole.
Add 1/2 onion rings on top.
Add the remaining mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: e-z fruit salad
directions: Mix together and stir in 1 package instant pudding (lemon and pistachio makes the best).

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with 2 cups crushed grahams.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat with mixer for no less than 15 minutes, eggs, 2 sticks margarine and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Spread mixture over cracker crust, then cover with bananas.
Spread drained pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cut up cherries.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order.
Bake crust 3 minutes at 400°.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Then bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Maybe not quite that long, keep checking the center.
When it cracks, it's done.

title: candy apple pie
directions: In mixing bowl, toss apples, candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour. Pour into pie crust.
Crumble second pie crust with 2 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° on a baking sheet, 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend
the first 9 ingredients together.
Place half in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Use remainder of mixture for second layer.
Top with crushed chips and grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coca-cola jello salad
directions: Heat the crushed pineapple; add lemon and cherry jello.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup juice from cherries; mix.
Add canned cherries, Coca-Cola and nuts.
Pour into mold and let set until firm.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add Pet milk and vanilla; make sure all sugar is dissolved.
Add rest of milk.
Pour this in the ice cream maker and close; start freezer.
Put ice around.
Layer salt and ice about 4 to 5 times until you get to the top.
You may have to add more ice and salt.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool; punch holes into cake.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Before serving, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and pineapple.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, then stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans, about 10 minutes.

title: braunschweiger cheese ball
directions: Let all soften to room temperature.
With mixer, mix all but cheese and mayonnaise until free of lumps.
Chill a few hours. When firm, form into 4 balls.
Chill again.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise so it is like an icing; spread on meat balls.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve on crackers.

title: strawberries with sour cream custard
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir one minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend small amount of milk mixture into eggs.
Blend egg mixture into milk mixture in saucepan.
Add sour cream and vanilla and beat with a wire whisk until well blended.
Cool immediately by placing in bowl of ice or cold water for a few minutes.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
To serve, spoon custard sauce over strawberries.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine applesauce and egg; stir well.
Combine flour, soda, sugar, salt and spices.
Add to applesauce mixture, stirring just enough to moisten the dry ingredients (overmixing makes tough muffins).
Stir in the melted margarine.
Toss raisins with an added 1 tablespoon of flour and fold into batter.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 18 medium size muffins.

title: "blackening" meat or fish
directions: Blackening is a way of cooking quickly with seasonings that turn black.

title: crunchy corn dogs
directions: You will need 12 skewers or other sticks.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: *Fresh glazed strawberries make an excellent topping.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream oleo and cheese together.
Add flour, salts and onion. Batter will be very stiff.
May use hands!
Add Rice Krispies and then form into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with a fork on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sometimes I form batter into long logs, chill and then slice in 1/4-inch slices.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Cook and separate ground beef in a large skillet.
Place in a roaster and add chopped onion, mushroom and chicken soups, water, rice, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350°F. for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring twice while baking.
It may need more water added.
Heat the chow mein noodles in the oven and put on top of casserole just before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat first five ingredients together.
Heat milk and butter, but do not boil.
Add to first mixture.
Bake at 300 for 30 minutes or until firm-(texture of jello).
Bake as custard or in 2 pie crusts.

title: black forest cake
directions: Make cake according to instructions on package, adding egg, oil and water.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan as directed.
Cool.
Mix pie filling with liquor.
Spread over cake; frost with whipped topping.
Decorate with shaved chocolate if desired.
Freezes beautifully.

title: mama's banana bread
directions: Mash 9 bananas and add eggs, salt, butter, sugar, soda, and add flour last.

title: brie and herb cheeses in pastry
directions: Lightly flour baking sheet.
Place pastry on sheet, roll gently and remove fold lines.
Place Brie in center of pastry. Spread 1 package of semi-soft cheese on Brie.
Turn Brie over and spread remaining semi-soft cheese on second side of Brie.
Bring pastry up around sides and over cheese, wrapping completely and trimming excess pastry, and place seam side down.
Gather pastry scraps and decorate top.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before baking.)

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix up jello and water.
Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Add chopped cherries.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk.
Spread over firm jello.
Top with chopped pecans.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix salt, zucchini, onions and pepper thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Rinse; drain. Place in large kettle. Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil. Pour over vegetables. Simmer until reaches a boil. Boil 30 minutes and then can. You may pack jars and process 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli first; drain.
Mix onion, mayonnaise, eggs and mushroom soup.
Layer broccoli mixture, then cheese, then repeat. Put crackers on top.
Sprinkle melted butter on top of crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in flour and cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla, juice and rind.
Combine well.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: baked potato fans
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, cutting to but not through bottom.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Drizzle with melted margarine and dill.
(You can use different herbs to your taste.)
Bake for 50 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: creamy mushroom rice
directions: Combine water, mushrooms, butter and bouillon cubes in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stir in rice.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and serve at once. Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon peach cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar and 1/4 pound butter (softened).
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Mix flour and baking powder together and set aside.
To creamed mixture, add flour and milk alternately.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Color 1/2 of the dough with red food coloring.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls, then in logs.
Twist 1 red and 1 plain log together in shape of a cane.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when they come out of the oven.

title: squash and pepper saute(serves 2)
directions: Cut the peppers in pieces big enough to skewer.
Combine the first set of ingredients and pour half of it over the potatoes, shallots and baby artichokes in a roasting pan and the other half over the rest of the vegetables in another dish.
Marinate for 4 hours.
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Bake the vegetables in the roasting pan for 30 minutes or so, basting with the juices every 5 or 10 minutes.
Remove from the oven and add to the vegetables in the bowl along with the marinade.
Using bamboo skewers, thread the vegetables and sprinkle with extra fresh rosemary.
Broil or grill the vegetables about 6-inches from the heat until the peppers are blistered and the tomato skins split, about 6 minutes on each side.

title: low-cal veggie dip(serves 2)
directions: Combine thoroughly, serve with raw carrots, celery, broccoli flowerets, mushrooms and other raw vegetables.
Approximately 40 calories.

title: brownie pie
directions: Bake shell for 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove shell and reduce temperature to 325°.
Melt chips and beat with remaining ingredients, except nuts, until smooth.
Add nuts and pour into shell.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Beat in oil, eggs and plums.
Beat with mixer 4 minutes, until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Makes 1 tube pan cake or 2 large loaves and 4 small loaves. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours (less for small loaves).

title: michigan sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer on low heat for 2 to 3 hours. Serve with hot dogs and onions on a bun.

title: fudge no-cook cookies for kids(grown-ups, too!)
directions: Boil butter or oleo, sugar and milk for 1 minute, no more, as it gets sugary.
Turn off heat.
Add to hot mixture the remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together well and drop on wax paper or greased pan.
Great.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix equal parts of grape juice and Sprite or ginger ale (may use sugar-free).
Freeze extra juice to be used in punch instead of ice.
Do not mix punch too far ahead of time.
Keep covered until time to be used.

title: brown sugar coconut cookies
directions: Pat out the size of a walnut.
Bake until brown.
Peanuts are good instead of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers and remove seeds.
Place in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Rub outside with oil. Brown beef in skillet with oil, onion and garlic.
Pour off any grease.
Mix with rest of ingredients and stuff peppers.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: taco spread
directions: Blend the cream cheese, cottage cheese and 1/2 package taco seasoning together with mixer.
Put in oval mound on serving platter.
Chop the green pepper, tomatoes and onions.
Spread over cream mixture.
Sprinkle other half of taco mixture over all.
Top with cheese and olives.
Serve with Doritos or taco chips.
Serves 8 to 12.
Very pretty dip.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well and add flour, sifted with salt and soda. Add oatmeal and nuts. Mix well and form in long rolls, chill thoroughly. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange glory rolls
directions: Boil the butter, sugar, orange juice and rind for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Place 1 Tbsp. mixture into each well greased muffin cup. Soften yeast in 1/2 c. warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water in large mixing bowl. Add 3/4 c. cold water. Cool to lukewarm
Blend in the eggs and yeast. Gradually add flour to form stiff dough; beat well. Toss on well floured surface until no longer sticky.

Roll out one-third at a time on floured surface to a 12 x 10 inch rectangle. Brush with melted butter. Roll as for jelly roll, starting with 12 inch edge. cut into 1 inch slices. Place in muffin cups, cut side down.
Let rise in warm place until light, 45 to 60 minutes. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 30 seconds, then invert, allowing sauce to drain onto rolls.

title: four-bean beef bake
directions: Brown ground beef with bacon in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: chicken hula
directions: Rub chicken with garlic; sprinkle with salt.
Broil or grill chicken until cooked through.
Drain pineapple juice into large saucepan.
Combine with honey, lime juice, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add pineapple slices.
Heat through.
Serve pineapple and sauce with chicken. Sprinkle with lime peel.
Serves 4.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pineapple and nuts.
In a small bowl, combine lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add to chicken mixture and mix lightly, adding more mayonnaise if necessary.
Cover and chill well before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab-mushroom sauce for pasta
directions: Saute in butter the onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Add flour, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Add half and half and cook until thickened.
Add crab; heat thoroughly.
Serve over your favorite pasta with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chicken vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Brown onions in butter.
Add flour and brown lightly to make a sauce.
Add milk and stir well. Add diced chicken, peas and carrots.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook beef until brown. Drain. Add spaghetti sauce and heat through.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in medium bowl and blend well. Spoon 1 1/2 cups meat sauce into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 4 uncooked noodles over sauce, half of the cheese mixture, 4 slices Mozzarella cheese, half the remaining meat sauce and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Pour water around sides of pan.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake 1 hour. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more or until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Line sheet cake pan and a regular cake pan with graham crackers.
Bring to a boil the oleo, butter and sugar; boil for 1 minute.
Add nuts and pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: tootsie bar
directions: Cream shortening, egg and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla. Spread mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Pat out until mixture is thin (almost covers cookie sheet).
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt 1 large chocolate bar in double boiler.
When cookies cool slightly pour chocolate and spread.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Prepare hens.
Split the breast (don't cut all the way; leave the back whole).
Place hens in a browning bag.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni by directions on box (do not let it get too brown). Cook about 3 minutes.

title: lemon juice pie
directions: In beater, put milk and lemon juice. Beat until thick. Add Cool Whip and beat until it almost stands in peaks. Put in graham cracker crust and sprinkle some graham crumbs on top. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: birming
directions: Place beef roast in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and cover.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Set cherries aside.
Combine cherry syrup, brown sugar, orange juice and cloves in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Make shallow cuts in roast in diamond shape designs and brush with cherry mixture.
Secure orange slices and cherries on roast with wooden picks.
Brush fruit with cherry mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, brushing every 10 minutes with remaining cherry mixture. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: beef balls stroganoff
directions: Lightly toss first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 18 meat balls. Brown in oleo.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes.
Remove meat balls.
In pan drippings, saute onion and drained mushrooms. Remove from heat.
Stir in mushroom soup.
Add meat balls.
Simmer until thoroughly cooked.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook stirring over low heat for 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the corn, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and milk. Fork in beaten egg yolks, then fold in beaten whites. Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole. Dot top with butter. Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven (350°) for about 45 to 50 minutes just until middle is set.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
This makes two 9-inch pies.

title: louisiana bean-burger casserole
directions: Cook the hamburger meat in a skillet or in the oven until it is done.
Drain the grease; then scramble the meat into small pieces. Put the meat into a large mixing bowl.
Add cheese, beans, catsup and water.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a large baking dish.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
At the end of this time, remove the casserole from the oven and stir the mixture to make sure all the cheese is melted.
(Since ovens vary, you may need to bake the dish another 15 minutes.)
When the cheese is melted throughout, place crisscross strips of cheese on top for decoration.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: black bean soup(low-fat)
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, bring 1/2 cup chicken broth to a boil over high heat.
Add the onions and garlic; reduce heat to medium.
Cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add the black beans, tomatoes, remaining 4 1/2 cups broth and cumin and bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat to low; cover again and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
After simmering, pour half the soup into a food processor or blender and puree until smooth.
Transfer back to the Dutch oven/saucepan; heat until hot and stir in cilantro and salt to taste.
In a small bowl, combine diced cheese and peppers.

title: crusty corn bread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add next two ingredients.
Heat bacon drippings in an iron skillet; pour half into cornmeal mixture.
Use rest for cooking.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: freezer french toast
directions: In shallow bowl combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture, coating all sides; let bread soak in mixture until as much liquid as possible has been absorbed.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat oil (or margarine).
Add bread and pour an equal amount of any remaining egg mixture over each slice.
