Reduce heat and cook until bread is browned on underside; turn slices and brown other side.
Transfer toast to a baking sheet; cool slightly, then freeze.
Once frozen, wrap toast slices individually or stack and wrap, using 2 sheets of wax paper between each slice to separate.
To serve, reheat in toaster or in 350° oven.
Can be frozen for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
Mix oleo, cocoa, oil and water in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and eggs, mixing well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: salsa chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put rice in baking dish.
Cover rice with water.
Pour 1/2 jar picante sauce in rice and mix well.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Pour remaining picante sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and jam. Mix well.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients with butter mixture. Add nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: southern green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; place bacon on paper towel to soak excess grease.
Crumble bacon.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon grease and put in skillet.
Get it fairly hot.
Add ham, onion, celery and garlic; cook until onions start to look transparent.
Pour ham mixture and bacon into a pan; add green beans with juice.
Cover pan and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add seasonings; continue to simmer over low heat until most of liquid is gone.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Make cake mix; bake and then cut cake into squares.
Mix dry pudding, dry Dream Whip and milk with electric mixer until thick and fluffy.
Mix orange juice and Kahlua; put aside.
Put 1/3 of the cake pieces in bowl you are going to serve in.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of Kahlua mix.
Add 1/3 chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of chocolate chips.
Top with one container of Cool Whip or until completely covered.
Repeat these steps two more times.
Garnish with cherries and chill for several hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine quick
oats
and
water,
let stand 20 minutes. Mix together brown
and white sugar, butter, egg, flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Double recipe if desired.

title: deanna's shrimp stir fry
directions: Into pan (I like to use an electric skillet) pour olive oil, shrimp, garlic powder and onion powder. Saute until shrimp are heated through. Add cocktail sauce and stir. Add frozen veggies. Stir together until heated thoroughly. Serve immediately while hot.

title: alan's linguine with clam sauce
directions: Put salted pasta water on to boil.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add juice from clams, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook until reduced to 1 cup-about 5 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice and enough mayonnaise to spread.
Add salt and pepper.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spray or butter a 2-quart pan.

Mix drained and rinsed sauerkraut, onion and sour cream. Pour into pan to cover bottom. Crumble a layer of corned beef on top. Grate or thinly slice Swiss cheese on top of corned beef. Toast rye bread and crumble on top until well covered. Drizzle butter over all. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot cube steak and gravy
directions: Turn meat in flour, salt and pepper, then brown in skillet in hot oil.
In crock-pot, mix together 1/2 cup flour with 6 cups water.
Stir in spices and Kitchen Bouquet, plus 2 teaspoons salt. Add meat to gravy and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as directed.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir.
When cheese is	melted,
add
remaining
ingredients except onions. Bake at 375° for
minutes.
Top
with onion rings and bake until hot.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart glass container.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High until light brown, usually 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice with a wooden spoon.
Stir in the remaining ingredients, saving soda for last until light and foamy.
Quickly spread on baking sheet.
Spread as thinly as possible for more brittle candy.
Butter may be used to prevent this from sticking to the spoon.
Cool candy and break into pieces.
Do not touch this with fingers; it will be very hot!

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Put ingredients in a double boiler over boiling water.
Cook for 7 minutes, beating constantly with an electric mixer.
Remove from stove and add your favorite flavoring.
Then spread on top and sides of cake.

title: waffles
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients together.
Place egg yolks and whites in separate bowls.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks. Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Stir in milk.
Combine milk and egg mixture with dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add shortening and fold in egg whites.
Ladle or pour batter onto hot waffle iron and bake until brown.
Makes 6 large waffles or more.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add above ingredients and simmer in pan for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: snowball cake
directions: Add cold water to soften gelatine.
Add boiling juice or water, fruit and sweetener; place in refrigerator until it starts to jell (about 1 1/2 hours).
Fold in 1 package whipped Dream Whip and angel food cake that has been broken in small pieces.
Press down in large bowl; place in refrigerator until firm.
Remove from mold and frost with other package of Dream Whip.

title: gorp (trail mix)
directions: Add as many of the combinations as you want or use your favorite items to make a nutritious snack for a hike.
Any dried fruits can be used.

title: mock duck
directions: Pound sirloin tips if they are too thick.

title: everyday oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix on medium speed the melted butter, vanilla, sugar and buttermilk.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; stir in oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Dip fingers into water; press dough down to 1 1/2-inch diameter. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will be light golden brown.
Remove cookies at once, or cookies will stick.
Place on cookie rack.
Cool.
Store airtight.
Makes approximately 10 dozen cookies.

title: christmas zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts and zucchini. Combine the rest; stir gently into the zucchini mixture.
Bake in 2 loaf pans that are pregreased and floured at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut up broccoli into bite size pieces.
Chop onion.
Add cherry tomatoes (whole).
Slice mushrooms.
Add artichoke hearts with oil.
Add a little Italian dressing and refrigerate.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cut up bacon; fry until crisp and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Boil 1/2 hour.
Put in blender; puree.
Salt and pepper to taste. Use as a drink, hot or cold, or as a soup.
Can be frozen.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using a 14 x 10 cake pan. While cake is baking, prepare the instant pudding and refrigerate. Let cake cool and spread pineapple on cake.
Combine cream cheese, cool whip and pudding and spread the mixture over the pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Dot with maraschino cherries and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.
This cake keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Add Hunts special sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add creamed corn.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: baked custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Easy, quick and delicious!

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 2 hours or until brown and tender.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine buttermilk, egg and shortening.
Mix well; add pepper and corn.
Pour immediately into a pan that has been greased and dusted generously with corn meal and browned.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook in small amount of water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients, except half the cheese and cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: king pou chicken
directions: Heat oils in wok and stir-fry chicken until tender and set aside.
Stir-fry scallions and garlic until tender (2 or 3 minutes).
Add vinegar, honey and ginger.
In separate bowl, blend arrowroot and tamari (soy sauce).
Add soy mixture to wok and stir until thickened.
Add back the chicken.
Coat chicken and serve over brown rice.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: Cook figs and sugar slowly for 1 hour; add Jell-O and cook 30 minutes longer.
Put in hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: dorothy's golden casserole
directions: Boil squash and mash.
Saute onion in vegetable oil and add broth to squash.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar to taste. Place in casserole and cover with grated cheese.
Cook medium oven until cheese is melted and boiling.

title: tarragon peas
directions: Cover peas with a little water and cook until crisp-tender and still a bright green.
Do not overcook.
Drain and add butter, salt, sugar and tarragon to the pan.
Toss gently.
Pour cream over the peas; heat through and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easter birds nest
directions: Put Shredded Wheat in large plastic bag and crush with rolling pin; put into large mixing bowl (lightly greased).
Melt butter and marshmallows over low heat in double boiler; when marshmallows are completely melted, pour over Shredded Wheat.
Mix well; shape into birds nests in muffin pans.
Fill with jelly beans.
Makes approximately 20 to 22 nests.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour sugar, salt and cocoa. Add egg yolks and a little milk. Mix until it is smooth. Add remainder of milk and cook on medium high. Add oleo and constantly stir the mixture until it is thick and bubbles. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour in baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff peak forms. Add 5 Tbsp sugar and beat again until stiff peak forms. Bake at 350 degrees or until golden brown.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Over a medium-low heat, melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add cream to the melted margarine.
Measure Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper; add them to the margarine and cream in the saucepan and stir.
To the heated liquids in the saucepan, add the cooked noodles and toss the noodles into the sacue until they are well coated.
Keep the noodles warm over a low heat until they are ready to be served.
When serving, place the noodles in a bowl with a serving spoon and place the bowl on the serving table.

title: chefs potato salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Combine and add dressing, mustard and salt.
Mix lightly; cover and chill.
Serve over lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges, olives, sliced mushrooms and sliced beets.

title: mississippi riverboat apricot salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg and juice over low heat.
Add butter; cool.
Fold in whipped cream and spread on jello.
Top with grated cheese.

title: fajitas(4 servings)
directions: Using a large bowl, pour dressing over chicken, green pepper, onion, garlic and oregano.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes; drain.
Stir-fry chicken mixture until chicken is browned.
Stir in tomatoes.
Wrap tortillas in dampened paper towels.
Microwave on High 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes to soften.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt tidbits in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles and mix well.
Add salted peanuts; mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Make 9-inch pie crust.

title: hot pumpkin nog
directions: Beat 1 cup sugar into egg yolks, then stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring.
Beat 3 tablespoons sugar into egg whites until they peak.
Mix whipping cream, cinnamon, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add to milk.
Cool 3 hours.
Top with egg whites.
Add dash of nutmeg.
Serves 8.
A holiday delight!
Enjoy!

title: smoked oyster roll
directions: Prepare the day ahead.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Press on foil; spread to about 1/3-inch thickness.
Should measure approximately 5 x 10-inches.
Refrigerate several hours.
Chop the drained oysters.
Spread along center of cheese mixture.
Roll up jell-roll style.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with wafers or any other crackers.

title: toasted pecans
directions: In heavy skillet melt butter.
Add pecans and cook until warm and well coated with butter.
Then spread out on large baking sheet and toast 10 to 15 minutes in 300° oven.
Place on paper towels with newspaper underneath.
While hot, salt; turn and salt again.

title: 7 level salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar and set aside.
Fry the bacon until crisp.
Drain it on a paper towel.
Crumble the bacon.
Shred the sharp cheese.
Combine lettuce, celery, green peppers, onions, peas and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle the crumbled bacon and cheese on top.
Cover and put in refrigerator to cool.
Let set for a while.
Great cover dish.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of crusts.
Whip the 2 packages of Dream Whip or use Cool Whip.
Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Mix with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Pour over bananas.
Top with pie filling.
Makes two pies.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add extract and coloring, if wanted.
Put through a cookie press and bake in 400° oven for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Be careful to watch so cookies don't get too brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with cookie slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread mixture over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with combined marmalade and water.
Chill.
Cut in wedges to serve. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Make into roll and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Slice and serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: white bread
directions: Combine potato flakes, hot water, sugar, salt and shortening. When lukewarm, sprinkle with yeast.
Add eggs and flour to knead. Let rise twice.
Make into 5 loaves and let rise in greased pans. Bake at 350° until nicely browned.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix powdered sugar, Crisco, margarine and milk together.
When fluffy, add vanilla, salt and lemon juice.
Mix well.
If you desire, color; add your food coloring.

title: dr. byrd cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make a well in center and break eggs into it.
Add oil, vanilla, bananas and last the pineapple with juice.
Stir, do not beat, until well blended (under mixing will ruin cake).
Pour batter into well greased (9 or 10-inch) tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 20 minutes.
Cake will crack on top.
Set pan on rack to cool.
Run knife blade around edges of pan and turn out to cool.

title: chocolate satin pie
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients on low heat until all blended. Remove from heat and add 4 egg yolks, one at a time.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in 4 beaten egg whites.
Pour in cooled pie shell.
Serve at room temperature with whipped cream.

title: cheesy-potato-soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cook 10 minutes.
Add stock and dill; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Puree the vegetable mixture adding cream cheese.
(A hand blender will allow you to blend in the same pan you are cooking in.)
Stir in milk and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with bread and salad for a delicious meal.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful into hot oil and fry like hush puppies.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat sweet milk; add butter.
Add salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Add oysters without juice.
Cook on low heat until the edges begin to curl.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Set uncovered in refrigerator overnight to dry. Roll tablespoonful into a ball.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: ice cream coffee cake
directions: Line bottom and sides of

9 or 10 inch spring form pan with lady fingers. Line sides first, then bottom. Combine ice cream and Heath bars until well blended. Pour in lined pan. Top with Cool Whip. For garnish, take potato peeler and make chocolate curls with Hershey bar. Refrigerate overnight. This is my absolute favorite birthday treat!

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375 - 400 for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend well and let it ripen.
Serve as a dip for fresh, crisp vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks in greased pan.
Place chicken on top.
Pour soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and oleo; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: hook's cafeteria brownies
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir (marshmallows will be partially melted).
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes (let stand 1 minute or until thickened).
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spoon into crust and arrange cookies over pudding mixture. Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: hot italian sausage and spinach pie
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and cool.
Cut into small pieces.
In small bowl, mix the reserved egg yolk with 1 teaspoon water.
In large bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust. Top with additional crust and brush with the egg and water mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes and top with hollandaise sauce.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan with shortening.
Arrange uncooked frozen rolls in Bundt pan. Sprinkle uncooked butterscotch pudding on rolls.

title: hummingbird muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in a large mixing bowl flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine eggs, oil, pineapple, bananas and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until just combined.
Fold in nuts.
Grease 12 jumbo or 30 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups until 3/4 full.
(This batter doesn't rise, it's heavy.)
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for jumbo or 20 minutes for 2 1/2-inch.
Remove muffins from tins and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 12 jumbo or thirty 2 1/2-inch muffins.

title: 5 layer casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish. Slice all vegetables and layer in order given.
Sprinkle a little hamburger on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and nuts.
Pack on bottom of a rectangle cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: seviche
directions: Cut raw fish into bite-sized pieces.
Sole, flounder, salmon, scallops or other ocean fish may be used.
Fresh water fish is not recommended.
Frozen fish may be used.
Cover fish with juice and allow to stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain well and toss with other ingredients.
Serve chilled on lettuce. Can be served as first course or as cold main dish.

title: marsha's russian tea
directions: Mix in container.
Shake before each use, because sugar settles to bottom.	Add as much per cup of hot water that your taste requires.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 15 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 3 cups flour and 2 tablespoons pure lemon extract. Mix well and fold in 7-Up.
Pour into a well greased and floured bundt cake pan.
Bake 1-1 1/4 hours or until cake test comes out clean. Do not overbake.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar or use a lemon glaze.

title: mexican beans
directions: Soak pinto beans for 3 to 4 hours.
Cook beans until tender. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: carol's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix to creamy consistency.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for exactly 8 minutes.
(They won't look done!) Remove from oven.
Allow cookies to rest for 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.

title: creamy dill dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with salad greens.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken and green apple fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken cubes in tequila, ancho chili, cumin, coriander, black pepper, garlic and olive oil for about an hour. Using a cast iron skillet or griddle, heat a little olive oil. Cook chicken on medium high heat, with marinade, until it is browned and liquid has reduced.
Add the other ingredients (except apples) and cook until chicken is thoroughly cooked and vegetables begin to become tender.
It is crucial to NOT overcook the chicken and vegetables.
Add apples and cook for 1 - 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.	May be served with warm tortillas, sour cream, diced tomatoes, grated cheese and fresh cilantro for garnish.

title: apple-black walnut cake with brown sugar glaze
directions: Mix corn oil and sugar until smooth.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and fold into apple mixture.
When thoroughly blended, pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour or until done.
Cool cake.

title: orange yogurt fruit dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese and stir in yogurt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve with apples, pears, kiwi fruit, bananas and grapes.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Dip zucchini in eggs and then in Dixie fry mix.
Fry in oil or butter in skillet.
Drain on absorbent towels.

title: rotel mexican dip
directions: In small pan, saute chopped onion in Ro-Tel juice.
In larger pan, slowly melt Velveeta.
Add soup and stir until smooth.
Add Ro-Tel, sausage, beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in crock-pot with tortilla chips.

title: kugel
directions: Heat butter and milk.
Add eggs, potatoes, onion, salt and pepper and mix well.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. The last 20 minutes sprinkle cooked sausage on top.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown and crumble sausage and ground beef.
Mix and put in a crock-pot on low.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Line a casserole with pie crust.
Mix sugar, spices and salt; sprinkle over apples.
Fill casserole with apples; add molasses, butter and water.
Cover with punctured pie crust; tuck edges together.
Press to sides of casserole.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
With a spoon, break up crust in pieces and fold them into apple filling.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes at 350° (or until apples are tender).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yoghurt and cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumber and slice it in half.
Remove the seeds by running a teaspoon down the center of the cucumber.
Chop very finely; mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
If desired, garnish with crushed mint.
Serve with rice or as a dip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broccoli and water.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
In a large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Add onion.
Saute until soft.
Add flour. Cook for several seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add milk, broccoli, salt, black pepper, paprika, celery seed and cayenne pepper; mix well.
Heat to serving temperature over low heat.

title: uncooked peanut butter bars(kids' delight)
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar and melted butter together.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with plastic wrap or foil. Spread mixture into bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate chips and oil. Spread onto peanut butter mixture and cool.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar and melted margarine. Press in an 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Beat until creamy the eggs, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread creamed mixture over crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot mexican chicken salads
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup cheese and next 8 ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill.
Heat 1/2 inch of oil in a large deep skillet until hot.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil (375°) until crisp and golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon chicken mixture evenly onto fried tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Place on baking sheets.
Broil 4 inches from heat 30 seconds or just until cheese melts.
If desired, garnish with thin avocado slices and cilantro.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together lightly the first 8 ingredients.
Form into meat balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until done. Drain off grease.
Place in Corning Ware dish.
Add catsup and hot water (this can be increased if needed).
Simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: mayme's boursin
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Whip until light and fluffy with mixer.
Add spices; whip an additional 30 seconds. Pour into bowl.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours to develop flavor. Serve with crackers or crisp bread.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Combine milk, crumbs, cheese, butter and seasonings.
Stir in yolks.
Fold in whites.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water; bake in slow oven at 325° until firm, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Beat the sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add the egg white and beat well.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until it comes just to a boil. Remove from heat and let cool until lukewarm (or until you can touch with your finger).
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper by the spoonful and let dry.

title: top ramen cabbage slaw
directions: Break
up
noodles
with rolling pin; do not cook.
Mix first 6 items together in jar and set aside.
Chop cabbage and onions. Add
nuts, seeds and noodles.
Pour dressing over all and toss. Chill.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute peppers, onions and celery.
Stir soup and water until smooth.
Stir all ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: brown sugar pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the flour, cornmeal, baking soda and salt into a mixing bowl.
Beat the eggs until foamy and stir them into the dry mixture.
Stir in the buttermilk and 1 cup of the milk.
Heat the butter in a 9 x 2-inch black skillet and when it is very hot, but not brown, pour in the batter.
Carefully pour the remaining 1 cup of milk on top of the batter, without stirring.
Place the skillet in the oven and bake 50 minutes or until set and baked through.
Slice into wedges.
Serves 8.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Combine Crisco,
butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour,
salt
and pecans last and mix.
Pinch off dough and roll into little balls.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to
minutes.
Roll
cookies in powdered sugar while hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag and shake each biscuit piece in the sugar mixture. Place in buttered Bundt pan (line bottom of pan with pecans, optional).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn.
Put in two-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream, onion and salt.
Spread over corn and beans.
Mix melted butter with crackers and almonds.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together and put in pie dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into 1-inch slices.
Combine butter and brown sugar in a sauce pan and cook on medium heat until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes, lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded coconut before serving. (Some people like to lightly brown the coconut in the oven after sprinkling.)

title: kabob marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add kabob meats and vegetables.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Use kabob marinade for basting.
Leftover marinade can be stored in refrigerator in a glass container.
This marinade can be used for all your grilling!

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt 1/2 can of Pet milk with caramels.
Take cake from oven and top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Then top with caramel mixture.
Add remaining half of cake batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: berdenes olive pot roast
directions: Brown chuck roast and onion in a little oil or shortening. Add rest of the ingredients cover and cook slow for about 3 hours.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Whip milk and lemon juice together well.
Add crushed pineapple and Cool Whip and stir together.
Pour into crust and chill.
Very good served partially frozen.

title: jiffy rhubarb
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Put chopped rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over rhubarb.
Sprinkle dry jello over top.
Distribute cake mix over all.
Pour the water over top.
Sprinkle melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend Miracle Whip, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.
Add to first mixture.
Chill 3 hours. Before serving, stir in shoestring potatoes (chopped hard-boiled eggs are optional).

title: okra soup
directions: Precook ham hocks.
Cook for 1 hour before preparing soup. Mix all the ingredients into pot with precooked ham hocks.
Stir together. Cook for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Put into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Put 1/4 cup beans and 1/4 cup meat on each tortilla.
Top with onion and cheese, fold tortilla.
Place on oven safe plate or casserole dish. Pour red or green chili sauce over burritos and garnish with remaining cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, vanilla, sweetener, egg and cold water.
Beat, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Heat Crisco with molasses.
When shortening is melted, remove from fire, cool and add sugar, cinnamon, cloves, soda (dissolved in very little hot water), beaten eggs, flour and raisins.
Bake in a moderate oven.
The raisins can be left whole, if desired. Bake about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate world fudge from hershey, pa
directions: Combine milk, butter or margarine, sugar and marshmallow cream in a heavy 2 3/4 quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Continue cooking and stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add chips and vanilla, stirring until chips are melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: pretend apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with spices, vanilla and lemon juice.
Crush Shredded Wheat.
Spray a pie plate with Pam. Put in a layer of Shredded Wheat; cover with a layer of apples. End with Shredded Wheat; spray lightly with Pam.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You may serve ala mode with nonfat frozen yogurt.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and other ingredients and pour into a greased 11 x 13 baking dish. Top with 1/2 cup margarine (I reduce to 1/4 cup margarine). Add 2 - 3 cups of crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: wackie cake
directions: Stir until smooth, place in a floured and greased oblong pan and bake in a moderate oven,350°, for 25 to 35 minutes depending on the size of the pan. Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil frozen broccoli for 5 minutes, drain well.
Beat eggs, stir in mayonnaise, mushroom soup, onions, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold in cooked broccoli.
Place entire mixture in casserole dish, bake uncovered in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with king size Fritos dip chips!

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Stir just until moistened. Spray muffin tins with cooking spray.
Fill with batter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: texas bean dip
directions: In casserole dish you plan to use, add bean dip on bottom, mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper and add, mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix and add, sprinkle together onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: pastry shells
directions: For ease in mixing have cheese and butter at room temperature. Mix well and chill for 1 hour or longer.
Shape into balls and press into miniature muffin tin.
Press to make a shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn out of muffin tin and cool.
You can fill pastry shell with anything you wish.
I fill with chicken salad, egg salad, pudding or fruit.
Freezes well.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then add all ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: onion and cheese chicken bake
directions: Melt butter.
Add seasonings.
Roll chicken in butter mixture until coated.
Cook for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Add fresh mushrooms.
Cook an additional 1/2 hour.
Add onion rings and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Cook chicken (salted) in crock-pot or pressure cooker or boil until tender.
Remove bones and chunk chicken to bite size. Put in taco shell and sprinkle with cheeses.
Top with dabs of sour cream.
Roll up and put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Put some of cream of mushroom soup in bottom.
Add a little water to rest of soup and pour over top of shells.
Heat in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In double boiler combine Eagle Brand milk, chocolate and salt. Cook and stir until thick.
Gradually add hot water.
Continue stirring and cooking until mixture thickens (2 to 5 minutes). Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill mixture in refrigerator and cool, then fold in whipping cream.
Pour into pastry shell. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: braised beef
directions: In Dutch oven pan, melt bacon fat and fry onions lightly.
Add meat.
When meat is browned, add remaining ingredients.
Pour 2 cups of boiling water over this.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. The meat comes out very tender with a nice brown gravy.

title: empanada
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Mix the flour in gradually until you form dough.
Make empanada right away and let rise for 1/2 hour on top of the stove.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a bowl and allow to sit at room temperature for at least 10 minutes for the flavors to blend. This sauce or salsa tastes better if made 1 or 2 days ahead. Store it in an airtight container in the refrigerator. Makes 2 cups.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Boil sausage about 20 minutes.
Clean (cut casing off) and slice into pieces.
Slice onions and saute them in oil.
Add the sausage and slightly brown.
Slice peppers and add to mixture. Lower heat and let them steam 30 to 40 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; simmer about 20 minutes.
Can serve over rice or Italian bread or in rolls for sandwiches.
This can be made a day ahead or left in a crock-pot for a party.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in steamer basket over boiling water; cover and steam 10 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.
Combine raisins and rum; set aside.

title: seafood stroganoff
directions: Heat butter in saucepan.
Whisk in flour and cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Do not let it take on color.
Remove from the heat and pour in chicken broth, whisking to blend well. Return to heat, bring to slow boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and cook and stir until sauce is smooth and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, Tabasco, garlic, onion and mushrooms and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes longer or until onion is tender.
Stir in crabmeat and shrimp; heat through.
Taste and correct seasoning.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream and heat; do not allow to come to a boil.
Serve over rice or in patty shells.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until thick and clear.
Set aside to cool.
Scald milk.
When lukewarm, add 1 tablespoon sugar and yeast.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk mixture.

title: all purpose rub
directions: Mix the spices thoroughly in a bowl.

title: 30 minute minestrone
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Saute onions in oil. Reduce heat and add garlic, spinach and water.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain mixed vegetables and Great Northern beans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature; mix together and roll in any shape you wish.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar on high speed for 1 minute. Gradually add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time beating until stiff peaks form. Spread meringue over hot filling sealing to edge of pastry. Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes for one 9 inch pie.

title: pre-pizza
directions: Slice English muffins in half.
Toast in toaster.
Top with sauce, spices and cheese.
Return to toaster just to melt topping. Serve!
Yum yum!
"I Like a Pizza" song goes well with your snack!

title: tex-mex chicken casserole
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken.
Cut into pieces and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and chili powder over chicken.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fully cook rice; add mushrooms and pimento.
Brown sausage; add to rice mixture.
Add cream soup.
Pour in empty can 3/4 full of half and half; mix thoroughly.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Ritz crackers.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in covered container and refrigerate several hours before serving (the older the better). Pour part of sauce over a block of cream cheese, at room temperature.
Serve with Triscuits, crackers or other varieties. Sauce stores well in refrigerator and seems to get hotter with age.

title: bread pudding
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine remaining sugar with eggs, salt, cinnamon and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat in milk gradually until all is well combined.
Brush bottom and sides of 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish with melted butter. Reserve 1 tablespoon of the raisins.
Sprinkle remaining raisins over bottom of baking dish.
Pour milk mixture over raisins.
Cut bread slices (crusts removed) in half diagonally.
Spread with butter.
Arrange on top of milk mixture, each slice slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle with rest of sugar and raisins.
Set dish in larger pan; pour boiling water into larger pan halfway up sides of baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until knife put in 1 inch from side of dish comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes. Good with cream and/or strawberry preserves.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well the ground chuck, soda crackers, salt and pepper. Pat 1-inch thick in dish.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cut into squares. Dip in flour and brown.
Place in baking dish or pan. Pour the chicken or cream of mushroom soup over top of meat. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Whisk egg slightly, blending in mayonnaise and soup.
Stir in drained broccoli, onion and cheese.
Turn into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
After about 15 minutes, cover slightly with foil so it won't burn too much.

title: chicken casserole for 8
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion and salad dressing well; pour over croutons.
Beat milk and eggs together and put over croutons.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Just before baking, add 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dona's chicken enchiladas
directions: Put 2 tablespoons each of chicken, cheese and onion on tortilla and roll up. Place seam side down in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Do all 12 this way. Then melt margarine and blend in flour; add broth and cook until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and chilies. Pour over tortillas in baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add 6 sliced onions.
Cover with lid and simmer for about 30 minutes. Add sugar and flour.
Stir and cook a few minutes, then stir in stock, salt (remember the Parmesan is salty) and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes. Taste now and adjust seasonings. Stir and cook 2 sliced onions in chunk of butter until caramelized.
Once crisp and brown, add to soup for color and taste. Toast bread and place in warm oven to dry out. Fill earthenware bowls with soup.
Place toasted bread on top of soup.
Let sink and soak up soup, then sprinkle with cheese. Broil a few minutes to brown cheese.
(May use casserole dish in lieu of bowls.)
Yields 6 servings.

title: steamed baked fish(rock cod, red snapper, tilapia, etc.)
directions: Marinate fish with salt and pepper to taste for 15 to 20 minutes.
Steam 15 to 20 minutes, in round or oval pan, covered with foil, on a wok with boiling water.
Sprinkle and rub, in slits, ginger, salted beans and onion.
Heat oil in another pan. Pour hot oil over fish, sizzling.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Cover and let stand.
In mixing bowl, combine salt, sugar, shortening and boiling water.
Cool to warm.
Stir in yeast, egg and flour.
Beat well.
Refrigerate until ready to use (2 hours or more).
About 1 1/2 hours before baking, grease baking sheet.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board.
Shape into rolls.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover with towel and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Preheat oven to 425°. Bake in preheated oven for about 10 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut deer steaks into strips about 1 to 1 1/2 inches wide and 3 to 6 inches long.
Place on cookie sheet; salt thoroughly on side facing up.
Put in refrigerator for 12 hours.
After 12 hours, turn strips over and salt again.
Put in refrigerator for 12 hours again.
Pepper both sides, more or less to taste.
Place on grill grate.
Cook over low heat (225° to 250°) for 6 to 8 hours, or until dry.

title: creamy chicken broccoli noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain off most of liquid.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through, then stir in tomatoes.
Good light meal.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat to boiling the juice of crushed pineapple and dark sweet cherries.
Pour over black cherry jello and set aside to cool. When cool, add Coke.
Place in refrigerator.
When begins to congeal, add chopped cherries and pineapple, chunked cream cheese and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: If you freeze chocolate chips first, they will hold shape better.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Trim green outer skin and the pink flesh from thick firm watermelon rind.
Cut into pieces of desired shape and size.

title: creamy braised chicken
directions: In Dutch over or large kettle, bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add pearl onions and boil for 3 minutes. Drain and rinse onions in cold water; peel and set aside. In same pan, saute sliced onions, carrots and celery in 1 Tbsp. of butter. Remove vegetables and set aside on serving platter. Add chicken to pan; brown on both sides. Remove and keep warm. Add wine, simmer until reduced to 1/2 cup. Stir in seasonings and broth. Return chicken to pan; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until chicken is done. Remove chicken to a vegetable serving platter; keep warm. Combine flour and milk until smooth; gradually stir into pan. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Return vegetables to pan, remove from heat; cover and set aside. In a non-stick skillet, saute reserved pearl onions and mushrooms and remaining butter until tender. Add pearl onions and mushrooms to serving platter. Remove bay leaf from sauce. Pour sauce over chicken and vegetables.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder & salt.
Add to mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll thin & cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 325° for about 12 minutes. Strickland

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut together.
Spread 1/2 cup of mixture between cake layers that have been cut with a string to make 4 layers.
Mix other 1/2 of mixture with the Cool Whip and spread over cake.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 days before eating.

title: drying fruit for decorations
directions: For the apples, cut 1/4-inch thick and soak for 30 minutes in a brine made from the juice of the lemons, salt and water.
Spread on parchment paper on a cookie sheet.
Bake 2 to 3 hours in a 200° to 250° oven.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; set aside.
Mix sugar with cream cheese.
Whip the cream and mix in jello.
Add the creamed cheese mixture to jello.
Melt oleo and mix with graham crackers. Put 1/2 of the cracker mixture in bottom of flat dish.
Add other ingredients and top with rest of crumbs.
Set in refrigerator to jell.

title: treebeard's butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 slightly beaten egg with dry cake mix and butter to moisten dough.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press mixture evenly in pan.
Beat the cream cheese with 3 eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in most of the powdered sugar gradually, until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325° if glass pan, and at 350° if metal.
(It may take longer, 45 to 50 minutes.)
Sprinkle remaining powdered sugar and/or pecans over top.
(It is also good if you sprinkle pecans over crust before pouring liquid mixture over crust.)

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters, saving the liquor, wash carefully and drain. Place oysters, liquor, salt, pepper and celery tops in pan.
Cook until edges of oysters curl.
Blend butter and flour and add to oysters with cream.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: frozen fruit salad(alaska)
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple (save juices).
Soften gelatine in juices; heat to dissolve.
Cool; set aside.
Add fruit to gelatine mixture.
Let set until soft set; add nuts and mini marshmallows.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipping cream (whipped).
Pour into mold.
A large tube pan works well.
Freeze overnight.
Will keep frozen for quite some time; to loosen from mold, set in warm water.
Turn onto plate and slice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and drain; mix together mayo, onion, mushroom soup, cheese and eggs.
Set aside.

In casserole dish put broccoli on bottom, then pour mixture, the crushed ritz crackers and pour on to, then melt margarine; pour over top of crackers and bake at 350° for 30 min or until cheese is melted and crackers are brown.

title: dilly beans
directions: Put green beans in pint jars and cover with water.
Put old lids on and pressure
cook
minutes.
Let cool and pour off water (this is why
you
use old lids first).
Add to each jar with beans garlic,
red
chile
pepper,
dill,
sugar
and mustard seed.
Bring the
brine
ingredients
to
a boil, then pour over beans in jars.
Put
on
new lids.
Cool pack for 10 minutes or steam off 10 minutes in pressure cooker.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together cream of celery soup, sour cream and mayonnaise, then combine with first batch of ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup and broth; pour over Veg-All and chicken.
Mix butter, flour and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked lemon walleye
directions: Cut fish in serving pieces.
Place in a greased baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: chili
directions: Cok beef, onion and celery; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for a couple of hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef in 2 tablespoons oil until all the red is gone, then add onions.
Saute for about 10 minutes.
Do not brown. Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Cook not less than 2 hours.
Just before serving, add cheese and stir.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: paradise fruit bowl
directions: Drain and reserve all juices; add enough water to make 6 cups of liquid.
In large saucepan, place liquid, extract and pudding mixes.
Bring to full boil.
Let cool approximately 30 minutes, then add all fruits except bananas.
Place in refrigerator until cool.
Before serving, slice bananas and mix carefully.
Very good.
Very attractive fruit salad.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; set aside.
While still warm, peel and cube potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar, celery seed, vinegar and onions and mix well.
Fry bacon until crisp and pour bacon and grease over potatoes; mix thoroughly.
If too dry, add a bit of hot water.
Put in serving bowl and serve warm.

title: 150 year old chocolate jumbles recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients together except baking soda.
Combine sugar, eggs, shortening and molasses.
Beat the dry and wet ingredients together with sour milk.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with doughnut cutter.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° on cookie sheet.
Frost when cool.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: almond rice pilaf
directions: In large frying pan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in rice, mushrooms, seasonings and green onion.
Cook, stirring, until onion and mushrooms are tender, about 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole (at this point, you may cover and chill).
Stir in broth and almonds and bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
(If chilled, allow 1 hour and 10 minutes.) Stir before serving.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a large 11 x 14-inch oblong pan or as near as you have. Do not grease.
Pour pie apples in, juice and all.
Pour in pineapple, juice and all.
Mix and spread around in pan.
Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut, then pecans over oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well; set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into beaten egg; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni; pour into a lightly greased 1 3/4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy salad
directions: Combine, whip together and chill.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix sifted ingredients alternately with milk to sugar and shortening mixture.
Stir in dates, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar well.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate bits over top.
Let stand until soft enough to spread.

title: cabbage-parsley toss
directions: Combine prepared vegetables; chill.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Garnish with additional onion rings.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together crushed Oreos and butter. Press into bottom of long Pyrex (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer in order given in a large casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in brown sugar, granulated sugar and 1/3 cup water.
Stir in biscuit mix and chocolate pieces.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: chocolate cream candies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate, remove toothpicks and place into other balls as you go. Return to wax paper.
If needed, spoon a small amount of chocolate mixture over toothpick holes.
Keep balls chilled until ready to dip.
Makes about 200 to 250.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill milk 1 hour in freezer. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Chill until partly thickened. Beat cheese with fork. Add sugar, lemon juice and vanilla to cheese. Whip milk until stiff. Put Jell-O in the milk and beat. Put cheese mixture in and beat until smooth. Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together and press in dish. Pour cheese mixture over graham cracker crust and chill.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg, slightly beaten. Add ripe, soft bananas, baking soda, flour and salt.
Mix well. Pour into baking cups and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding(this was my only "success" in navajoland.)
directions: Combine.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can double.

title: classic chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, sugar, butter, vanilla and pudding in large bowl.
Beat in eggs; gradually add flour mixture.
Add chips.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased and floured muffin pans or loaf pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick to see if done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute sausage with onion and garlic.
Mix all ingredients together and moisten with a little white wine.
Pull off stem and pack mushrooms to overflow; press down.
Cook 10 minutes, covered with foil, and 10 minutes without in a 375° oven.

title: potato crisps
directions: Line a large baking sheet with foil.
Spray the foil with nonstick coating.
Arrange the potato slices in a single layer on the baking sheet.
Sprinkle with the garlic salt.
Bake in a 450° oven about 20 minutes or until the potatoes are crisp and golden. Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon topped potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice and soup in a large Dutch oven and cook slowly for 4 hours, stirring once in a while.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, using your own seasonings.
Skin and debone; cut into pieces and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Spray dish with Pam first.
Mix one can cream of celery and one can cream of chicken with 1 1/2 soup cans of water and pour over chicken.
Put 1 package of stuffing mix over top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Melt one stick of margarine and drizzle over the top of stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Stir gelatin and boiling water together until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Drain fruit well and add pineapple juice, blueberry juice and the flavored gelatin mixture.
Cool until syrup consistency.
Fold in the fruits.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions and fold into gelatin mixture along with nuts.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf for salad or doily for dessert.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain half of the liquid from each can of beans. Mix all ingredients and cook in a slow cooker.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar, white sugar, peanut butter, eggs, Karo syrup, vanilla and soda.
Add and mix by hand the oatmeal, Rice Krispies, chocolate chips and the M&M's.
Take a tablespoon of dough, roll it into a ball with your hands.
Drop onto cookie sheet and press out flat with your hands.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.
These freeze well.

title: squash souffle
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt and sugar.
Simmer with small amount of water for 20 minutes.
Drain well and mash with potato masher.
Add eggs, melted butter, flour, milk and cheese.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Bake in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole for 30 minutes.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Bake uncovered.
This can be stored in refrigerator unbaked for 2 or 3 days.
Freezes well unbaked.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cyndi's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients, except bacon. Pour into large baking pan.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dust raisins, apples and walnuts with some of the flour; set aside.
Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to egg mixture.
Fold in raisins, apples and nuts.
Pour into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Make sauce; pour over cake while still hot.

title: sourdough bread
directions: After you've completed the second step and have removed 1 cup of the starter from the refrigerator, add flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and oil to remaining sourdough.
Stir until smooth and flour is completely absorbed.
Dough should be just firm enough to gather into a ball.
If necessary, add 1/2 cup additional flour, stirring until all flour is absorbed.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: easy quick snack mix
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Great non-messy travel snack.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in next 3 ingredients and let stand 20 minutes (or longer) in refrigerator.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in wok until hot.
Stir-fry chicken 2 to 3 minutes or until white. Remove from wok or push up on sides.
Add remaining oil.
Stir-fry onion 1 minute.
Add celery.
Add pea pods; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Return chicken to bowl of wok.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; cook until thickened.
Stir in cashews.
Garnish with green onion.
Serve with fried rice.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water: stir in other ingredients (1/2 c. pecans). Chill.

title: church cookies
directions: Dissolve 3 tablespoons soda and 1 teaspoon salt in hot water. Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips over low heat.
Add confectioners sugar and canned milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
Mix soup, cream cheese and horseradish by hand, then stir in shrimp.
Serve with bagels for dipping.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarter pieces.
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
In Bundt pan, layer meat, hot mixture, biscuits and cheese.
Cook at 375° until brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut
carrots
in diagonal slices.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain
and
cool.
Cut
onion
in
rings.
Cut pepper
in strips.
Combine undiluted soup, sugar, oil, vinegar,
salt
and pepper.
Bring to a boil point.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour this over carrots and vegetables in a large bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Keeps well in refrigerator at least 10 days.

title: cheesy baked hash browns
directions: *Additional ingredients if desired.

title: chicken and spanish rice
directions: Boil hen until tender; remove skin and bones.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Return to 2 cups of broth for each cup of yellow Spanish rice used.
Boil until rice is tender; stir in garden peas and pimento.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Make stuffing according to package directions.
Get a ball of ground meat (between golf ball and baseball size) and flatten into your hand.
Make it into kind of a cup shape and place a ball of stuffing (a little smaller than a golf ball).
Wrap and seal meat around stuffing.
Repeat until meat is gone.
Place meatballs in skillet to brown, and then transfer into crock pot.
Open cans of soup and put in the bowl.
Stir until creamy, adding about one can full of water.
Pour over meatballs and cook on high for at least one hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Bake in well-greased and floured cake pans.
May use two or three layers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon cutouts
directions: Make into a paste; roll out flat and cut out desired shapes. Put hole in the top with the end of a straw.
Bake in preheated oven at 150° for 2 hours, keeping door open slightly.
These are a lot of fun to make at Christmastime and hang on tree or use on gifts, etc.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Put whole cranberries, sugar and walnuts in pie plate.
Beat eggs; add Bisquick, sugar, melted oleo and almond extract.
Spread over cranberries.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream the 3/4 cup sugar and oleo with a wooden spoon.
Beat in the egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Stir until well mixed.
Combine the 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place balls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Stir water, sugar and butter or margarine in a large saucepan over a medium heat until sugar and butter or margarine are dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until a few drops tested in cold water produce a soft, crackable thread (261° on thermometer). Pour onto greased tray.

title: holiday chocolate fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, milk, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in candied fruits.
Turn into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Chill until fudge is firm; cut into squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, margarine, powdered sugar and almonds in a medium bowl with fork until crumbly.
Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased, rectangular 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.
This will be the base of the dessert.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with nuts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix vegetable soup mix and sour cream; chill for 12 to 24 hours.
Delicious with raw vegetables; keeps well in refrigerator.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Partially thaw.
Add 1 (3 liter) bottle ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 50.

title: quick nut potica
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside in warm place till foamy.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, yeast mixture and vanilla.
Add half of the flour and the sour cream.
Then continue adding the rest of the flour to make a soft dough.
No need to refrigerate or raise the dough.
Roll out immediately and spread with filling and roll up.
Place in well-greased pans and prick tops with a fork in several places.
Cover and let rise for about 40 minutes or more.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes; test for doneness and bake a little longer if necessary.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth. Add peanut butter and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crumb crust.
Freeze.
Slivers of grated chocolate may be placed on top.
Serve directly from freezer and keep in freezer.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter or margarine, granulated and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Add semi-sweet chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in tightly covered jar.
Serve 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of mix in cup of hot water.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in lightly greased baking dish.
Combine soup and soup mix until smooth.
Spoon half mixture over rice.
Top with chicken, meaty side up, and add salt and pepper.
Add remaining mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: crock-pot beef burgundy
directions: Pour all ingredients into crock-pot and cook on medium (300°) for approximately 4 hours.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Layer on top of Cool Whip.
Chill and top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix together well.
Bake and serve.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg, salt, pepper and 1 can tomato sauce; form into loaf.
Place in a 7
x 10-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 crumbs with brown sugar and margarine.
Line pan with this.
Sift flour and salt.
Add hot milk.
Add egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla; pour on crumbs.
Cover with egg whites (mixed with remaining sugar) and beaten until stiff.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven until egg whites are brown.

title: saucy asparagus
directions: Heat soup and milk to boiling.
Add asparagus and pour into greased dish.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until tender. Add cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Then add onion rings and press down into mixture.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown.

title: best fresh pack dills
directions: Wash cukes and slice into spears.
Combine enough lime water to cover (basic amount is listed) and put cukes in large (5-gallon plastic bucket works great!) container.
Cover with lime water. Let soak overnight, drain and rinse several times to remove any traces of lime.
Pack spears into quart jars, adding 1 to 2 cloves garlic, 3 heads fresh dill or 1 tablespoon dill seed per quart and 1 to 2 small fresh whole jalapenos.
Combine vinegar, salt, water and sugar (if desired).
Bring to boiling.
Pour into jars, seal and adjust rings.
May be processed 10 to 15 minutes in boiling water bath canner.
Best served ice cold.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound meat with mallet to 1/4 or 1/2-inch thick.
Put flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Place meat in bag and shake to coat. Place meat in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine tomatoes, onion and parsley flakes.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly.
Microwave at 50% for 25 minutes.
Turn meat over; microwave 25 to 35 minutes or until meat is tender.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: quick & easy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix together pudding, sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
After mixing together, get another large bowl.
Put a layer of Nilla Wafers to cover bottom of dish.
Put pudding mixture in to cover cookies.
Continue to repeat layers until all of the pudding mixture has been used.
Top with crushed Nilla Wafers.

title: barbecue grill potatoes
directions: Cut potato into 4 slices. Place slices on square of aluminum foil (to wrap and bake potato in). Place oleo or butter on the slices with chicken bouillon sprinkled generously over that. Wrap aluminum foil around the potato and place in coals of barbecue for one hour.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients and pour into casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix together 3 cups flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
In a small saucepan, combine 1 3/4 cups water and oil. Heat to 125°.
With a wooden spoon, stir oil and water into flour mixture.
Add enough flour to make a firm, soft dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes on floured surface.
Cover with plastic and let rest 10 minutes.
Makes 8 (6-inch) crusts.
Top with desired topping.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes at 500°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350 degrees for 55 or 60 minutes in 13 x 9 inch pan.
Batter will be real thick, add cinnamon, if desired.

title: mint lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Then add lemon juice, raspberry juice, strawberry juice, water and mint sprigs.
Allow to stand for better flavor.

title: green salad
directions: Mix vegetables together and add 1 tablespoon of sugar with 1 1/2 cups of Miracle Whip.
Spread over top of vegetables, then spread top with a layer of grated cheese.
This makes a very large salad.

title: christmas eve salad(ensalada de nochebuena)
directions: Put lettuce in a large shallow bowl and arrange beets, oranges, apples, bananas, pineapple and limes over it.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Sprinkle pomegranate seeds and chopped peanuts over all.
Mix oil with vinegar and salt to taste.
Just before serving, pour over salad and mix gently.
Serves 8.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spaghetti dinner for 200 people (plus)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together; bake in a 300° oven, in a large roasting pan, for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: holiday yam bake
directions: Drain yams and pineapple.
Put into casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients except marshmallows.
Pour over yams.
Bake 30 minutes on 350°.
Take out and cover with marshmallows.
Cook for 10 or 15 minutes longer or until marshmallows are light brown.

title: toffee treats
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and egg yolk.
Blend in flour and vanilla.
Pat dough 1/2 inch thick on a greased cookie sheet.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate chips.
Cover with chopped nuts. Serve warm!

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: In pot combine potatoes with enough water to cover by 1-inch. Over high heat bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain; return to pot. Mash until smooth; cool 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°. Butter 1-quart casserole dish. Melt 1/4 cup butter. In a large bowl lightly beat in vanilla, melted butter and reserved mashed potatoes. Transfer to casserole dish. Combine sugar, pecans and flour; with fingers, work in remaining butter until pea-sized crumbs form. Sprinkle crumbs over potato mixture. Bake until top is bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat the eggs in a separate bowl. Combine the ingredients; add to beaten eggs. Place in casserole and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken-n-a-poke barbecue
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients except chicken.
Grease the inside of a medium size heavy paper sack and place in roaster pan.
Salt and pepper the chicken, dip in the sauce and place in sack along with remaining sauce.
Carefully fold sack in drugstore fold so as not to leak.
Cover roaster; cook 15 minutes at 500°.
Lower to 350° and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open sack until full cooking time is completed.

title: blue cheese butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl using an electric mixer or food processor.
Store well covered in refrigerator.
May also be frozen.
Tastes great on burgers.

title: cold pork salad dressing
directions: Beat egg.
Add all of the ingredients gradually; cook until thick.
Goes great on cold roast pork sandwich.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix in blender at medium speed the first four ingredients and syrup from pineapple 30 seconds or until smooth.
Turn into bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix carefully.
Spoon into aluminum foil lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan.
Freeze.
Unmold, slice and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: rich 'n creamy milk shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover.
Blend at puree speed until smooth, thick and frothy, 1 to 2 minutes. (Check after 45 seconds.)
Makes 1 large shake (about 1 cup).

title: frosted butter cookies
directions: Blend first five ingredients until well combined.
Form into small balls and refrigerate 1 hr.
Place on cookie sheet covered with parchment paper.
Flatten each ball with thumb.
Bake at 350 F for 15-17 minutes.
Cookies should be just golden on bottom and not at all browned.
Cool completely.
Mix next 4 ingredients, blend well, frost cooled cookies lightly.

title: banana oatmeal cookies(soft banana-flavored drop cookies)
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; beat in egg and banana.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend in.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until lightly browned and no imprint remains when touched (10 to 12 minutes).
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Amount:
5 dozen.

title: chicken squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls. Place in microwave bowl and heat until cheese is softened and mixture can be blended smoothly; set aside. Each package of dinner rolls will make 2 large squares. Press seams of dough flat; separate into squares. On cookie sheet, place 4 squares; top with chicken mixture. Place 4 more squares on top of chicken mixture. Press around edges to seal 4 squares. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in mixture of sugar (white) and cinnamon.
Toss into greased Bundt pan.
Add remaining white sugar and cinnamon.
Boil margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into buttered casserole.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Use pastry blender or use fingers to mix until crumbly, about the size of peas.
Crumble over peaches.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: bagogii
directions: Slice meat very thin and put in a bowl.
Slice onion thin and chop green onions.
Add to meat.
Julienne carrots to matchstick size.
Add carrots and all other ingredients except rice to meat. Mix well.
Heat up a large frying pan until very hot.
Add meat mixture and stir-fry until done.
Spoon over hot white rice and serve.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour and soda.
Does not need to be chilled.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch on High in the microwave for 3 minutes; stir and cook 2 minutes more.
Then add the jello and strawberries and stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: berry cheese cake pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Spoon pie filling atop.
Chill until set.

title: guacamole
directions: Smash the three avocados until there are no lumps.
Dice the tomato and onion and then add them to the avocados.
Stir them and add the lemon and salt.
Chill, then serve.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring 1 cup water and 1/2 cup margarine to boil. Add 1 cup flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball. Cool. Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon or mixer. Spread on cookie sheet, 11 x 15, or 2 round ones. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool. Don't prick.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and bell pepper. Saute.
Add cheese. Stir until melted. Add tomatoes and chicken. Stir.
Add noodles and stir.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake approximately 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In top of double boiler, mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt. Add slowly the boiling water, stirring to mix well.
Place over the double boiler pan; cook for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slightly beat egg yolks; add grated rind and juice. Add slowly to cooked mixture and continue cooking for about 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat; set aside and add 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover with meringue after pouring in already baked shell.
Make meringue of 3 egg whites (beaten stiff).
