Add gradually the sugar and salt.
Bake meringue covered pie for about 15 minutes in 320° oven.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except for the carrots.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
When the onion is translucent, the sauce is done.
Add the carrots and the dish is ready to serve.

title: wild duck
directions: Cut ducks into bite-size pieces, no bone, no skin.
Dredge in flour well seasoned with salt and pepper.
Saute in butter, adding onion, bay leaves, mushroom caps and pepper rings as meat is browning.
Add water and wine and simmer for 1 hour.
A pair of mallards will serve 3 to 4 people.
Can be served over wild rice, noodles or plain rice.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until tender in 2 cups of water.
Add mushrooms, salt and garlic salt.
Let simmer 1 minute.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk and stir into hot ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter and cheese.
Simmer until butter and cheese are melted.
Makes 6 cups.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers, bell peppers and onions.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seeds and salt together and pour over the vegetables.
Put in small bags and you may freeze.

title: blender breakfast
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Pour into a tall glass.
Each 1 glass serving contains 1 gram of fat and 202 calories.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Spread 1 can of beans in the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch dish. Layer half of the olives, half the salsa and half of the cheese. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Garnish with sour cream, sliced green onions and shredded lettuce, if desired.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in a little oleo.
Spread uncooked rice evenly in an oblong baking dish.
Put chops on top. Put one slice of tomato, onion and bell pepper on top.
If you don't have tomato and pepper on hand, onion alone will do.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 1 egg and melted oleo, then add other egg and mix well.
Add vanilla and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift first four ingredients together, then add peanut butter; beat well. Pour into a well greased loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and stir with crackers; let dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: glenno's favorite date nut cake
directions: Combine dates, soda, and boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream shortening then gradually add sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add flour and salt to shortening mixture alternating with the date mixture. Pour into a greased 8 x 12 Pyrex baking dish.
Top with chopped walnuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375 for 45 minutes.

title: slow-cooker venison roast with vegetables
directions: Cut wedges into roast.
Sprinkle soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce over roast; let stand for 1 hour.
Add seasoned meat tenderizer and garlic flakes.
Wrap roast in bacon slices and place in cooker.
Add potatoes, carrots and sliced onion.
Mix beef bouillon according to directions and pour into bottom of cooker.
Cover and cook on slow heat for 6 1/2 hours or 3 1/2 hours on high heat.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: man-style meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.
Pack into greased loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until crisp on top.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Finely chop pecans.
Mix first 6 ingredients; put in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Makes 1/2 cup.
Contains 19 calories per serving.

title: date balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together; cook for 10 minutes on low heat (slow boil stage).
Easy to scorch; stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add the Rice Krispies.
Chill mixture.
Shape into balls (size of walnut).
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in the skin.
Peel and shred; fold in other ingredients and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients adding 1 tablespoon of salsa.
Spread mixture evenly on soft tortillas.
Roll tortillas up and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Serve with remaining salsa to use as dip.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Blend cream cheese and tomato soup over low heat until smooth (use wire whisk).
Add celery, onions, mayonnaise and gelatin to chopped shrimp; blend with rubber spatula.
Pour into large mold.
Make at least 1 to 2 days ahead.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, rice, onion, green peppers, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well to blend.
Shape meat mixture into balls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place meatballs in slow cooking pot.
Pour soup over meatballs.
Cook on slow for 3 to 4 hours, or until rice is fully cooked through.

title: shrimp dressing
directions: Saute sausage, shrimp, celery and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Stuff mixture into chicken or turkey, or bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator a few hours before serving.
You may also add zucchini, broccoli buds, cauliflower or artichoke hearts.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Add beans and hot water. Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 1 hour. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add additional water during cooking if necessary. Remove 1/4 cup of beans. Mash and stir half into soup to increase consistency.

title: stuffed pepper
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut off tops and clean out.
Chop tops.
Place peppers in 2 quarts of salt water.
Bring to a boil, cover and then reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain peppers and set aside.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; remove bone and skin. Flake in a large mixing bowl. Add mashed potatoes and eggs. Mix well. Add bell peppers and onions. Form into palm-sized balls. Roll each ball in the corn meal. Cook in hot oil over medium high heat until browned.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach using package directions, omitting salt and margarine. Drain; squeeze out all liquid. Finely chop spinach, onions, watercress and parsley in a food processor or chop with a knife and transfer to a blender. Process just until blended; mixture should be coarse. Transfer to colander to drain excess liquid. Puree remaining ingredients in processor or
blender. In a medium bowl, combine the two mixtures, stirring well. Cover and refrigerator for at least one hour to allow flavors to blend. Serves: 12 (2 tablespoons per serving).

title: bottoms up berry cake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine gelatin and berries; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients at low speed; then beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Spread batter over marshmallows; spoon gelatin-berry mixture over batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Berries sink and marshmallows will rise.

title: chicken salad with bacon
directions: Tear lettuce into large pieces; place in salad bowl.
Add pepper, cucumber, mushrooms and chicken; toss lightly.
Top with eggs and bacon.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Do not use cake mix with pudding.
Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Press mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes and refrigerate overnight.
Peel and grate. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese slices, and mix.
Spoon into casserole dish with
a lid.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven.
Place cheese slices on top.
Replace lid and cheese will melt.

title: donut holes
directions: Mix the ingredients together well.
Heat the oil to 375° in a deep fryer.
Drop the batter into hot oil by spoonfuls.
Lift out with slotted spoon when brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar or granulated sugar.

title: huckleberry bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, butter, milk, flour and baking powder. Fold in huckleberries.
Place in 3 small loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread; cool.
Crumble in large bowl.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: nancy's vegetable pop-corn
directions: Wash and cut up all vegetables.
In a small bowl, mix cornmeal, flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Put vegetables in this mixture and coat real good.
Drop into hot deep fryer (oil to cover).
When vegetables float to top of oil, they are done.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Melt marshmallows in milk in double boiler and then mix well.
Put in Bundt pan and chill.

title: cheddar cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and Cheddar.
Add the flour, salt, red pepper or Tabasco sauce and walnuts. Shape into log rolls as round as 50 cent pieces.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice thin. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except M&M's.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and place 2 M&M's on each cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna.
Hand mix with chopped onion, cream cheese and liquid smoke.
Form into a ball and roll it in crushed pecans. Great on crackers.
Try with salmon, too.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, celery and bell pepper in skillet; drain. Place rice and chicken broth in medium size saucepan.
Add meat mixture and cook until rice is done.

title: one-pot pork chop supper
directions: Brown chops. Pour off fat.
Add other ingredients. Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In medium bowl or jar combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls mixture in mug.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar; let this set overnight.
Next day add sugar and eggs.
Beat all together with a whisk until thickened.
Do this over a low heat on the stove until it boils.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken pieces in a baking dish or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Pour vegetables over chicken.
Mix broth with soup.
Heat to boiling and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix margarine, biscuit mix and buttermilk.
Spoon over chicken and broth mixture. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef log
directions: Mix together thoroughly the meat, salt cure, mustard seed, garlic salt and smoked salt.
Refrigerate this in an airtight container.
Remove it each day for three days and remix, this helps to distribute the cure better.

title: deanna's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and set aside. If using kielbasa slice into quarter-sized pieces and set aside. Put olive oil into pan. Wash and slice potatoes and onion into pan.

Cook until done. Add hamburger or kielbasa, soup and milk. Heat together with garlic powder. Add cheese. It is done when cheese is melted and mixed together with the rest of the ingredients. Shredded cheese can be sprinkled on top for a colorful touch.

title: au gratin vegetables
directions: In 1-quart Pyroceram casserole, combine broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, carrots, onion and water.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring once. Set aside.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald 1 cup milk in top of double boiler over direct heat; slowly shake in the corn meal, stirring until the mixture begins to boil.
Set the pan over boiling water; cook for about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the molasses, sugar, butter and seasoning.
Add raisins; mix well.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with softened ice cream as a sauce.

title: crab salad
directions: In a medium skillet, saute the green pepper and onion in the butter for 3 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in imitation crabmeat, and saute for another 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and put mixture into a medium bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
May be served warm or cold.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together the lemon jello, hot water and the cold water and let partially set up.
Add the sliced bananas and crushed pineapple.
Mix together egg, sugar, cornstarch and the saved pineapple juice.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, mix with jello and top with the grated cheese.
Use a 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: christmas party punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on cans.
Mix all ingredients well.
Serve in punch bowl over ice.
Serves 50.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; roll dough into rectangle shape.
Spread apples over dough; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Place in a baking dish with 1 stick of melted butter.
Mix 1 cup of sugar with 1/2 cup water and pour syrup over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Great with ice cream.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion with garlic in oleo in skillet.
Add ground beef. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; heat to serve.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into large greased casserole or 2 small casseroles.
Mix extra butter with 2 cups torn breadcrumbs or mashed cornflakes.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbling and done.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry angel dessert(our favorite easter dessert)
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in 1 1/4 cups boiling water. Add strawberries; stir.
Scrape crust from cake.
Tear cake into small pieces and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour jello mixture over cake.
Punch cake down and refrigerate.
Top with custard sauce.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Melt Crisco in skillet.
Fry peppers and onions for 3 minutes in shortening.
Add meat and blend thoroughly.
Add seasonings. Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Mix well.
Put 1 cup of corn in casserole dish, then 1/2 of meat mixture.
Next, add a layer of tomatoes.
Repeat layers with corn, meat mixture and tomatoes. Cover with crumbs.
Dot with bits of Crisco.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Combine jello with hot water.
Add ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Combine undrained pineapple, nuts and sliced banana. Pour into mold.
Makes 1 quart.

title: kat's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix other ingredients with broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs; dot with butter and small amount of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk vanilla and mashed bananas.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, oil, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until done.
Cut in half lengthwise and take out yolks.
Mix egg yolks with mustard, relish, salt and black pepper. Add mayonnaise to taste.
Mix well and place back in egg halves. Garnish with a sprinkle of paprika and parsley sprigs.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in bowl.
Keep warm.
Set aside. Brown bacon; remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add flour and blend.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper. Stir until thick like a white sauce.
Add cream and bacon; pour over potatoes.
Add celery seed while mixing.

title: king cake
directions: Combine the two loaves of thawed dough into one by kneading them together.
Place dough in buttered bowl and turn dough to butter the top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 30 minutes, or until dough is doubled in bulk.
Punch the dough down and turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll into a rectangle about 25
x 10 inches.
Brush melted butter onto rolled out dough, leaving 1/2 inch border around edges.
Combine cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle evenly over butter.
Place almond (or baby) in the center of the dough, press lightly.
Starting at the long side, roll up dough. Moisten the finished edge with water and pinch seam lightly to seal.
Place dough, seam-side down, on buttered baking sheet.
Bring the ends of the dough together to form a circle. Moisten ends with water and pinch edges firmly together to seal.
Cover. Let rise in a warm place for about 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to a wire rack; cool completely before frosting.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add molasses and sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in sugar.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Place all ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir frequently until all ingredients are blended well. Serve warm with Tostitos Scoops.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Flavor with frequent portions of recreation and a dash of happy memories.
Stir well and remove any speck of jealousy, temper or criticism.
Sweeten with generous portions of love and keep warm with a steady flame of devotion.
Never serve with a cold shoulder or a hot tongue!
Finally, remember this prayer:
"Teach me this, O Lord, to know that true love is caring and sharing."

title: hot wings
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 360°.
Fry wings to golden brown. Drain.
Melt equal parts of butter and Tabasco sauce and pour over wings.
Sprinkle dry Ranch dressing mix over wings.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven in shallow baking pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix until coarse crumbs.
Beat 1 egg yolk; add water to make a cup.
Add to flour mixture.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix other ingredients.
Put cheese on top; bake 20 minutes.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Peel eggs and chop.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Add mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well.
Divide egg mixture between 4 slices of bread and spread with table knife. Top with remaining 4 slices of bread.
Makes 4 sandwiches. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cheese.
Stir in pineapple and 7-Up, strawberries and grapes.
Place in dish and put in freezer until starts to thicken. Whip cream and add to marshmallows.
Add both to other mixture. Freeze.
Take from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: nettie's potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick of butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread potatoes in pan.
Mix sour cream, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs on top. Top with 1 stick of melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: eggs benedict
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat 1-inch of water to boiling.
Break 1 egg into a small dish.
Slide egg into water, tipping dish toward edge of pan.
Repeat with remaining 5 eggs.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until eggs are just soft-cooked, about 3 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon; place in pan of warm water to keep warm.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off excess fat.
Add chili powder and onion.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and 1 1/2 cups water; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all and shape into individual loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes before glazing (pour off excess fat).

title: baked turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients until just blended.
Do not overmix. Press the mixture into 4 x 9-inch nonstick loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls 1 tablespoon of mix.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chocolate yummies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat; cool. Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Stir in egg, milk, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in coconut and drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Spread tops with buttercream frosting or chocolate frosting.
Decorate if desired.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Remove
casing
and
brown
sausage.
Remove
sausage; drain and
reserve
tablespoon drippings.
Saute onion and garlic
in drippings.
Add beef broth, water, wine, tomatoes, carrots, basil, oregano, tomato sauce and sausage.
Bring all to a
boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes uncovered. Skim fat
from soup and stir in zucchini, tortellini, parsley and pepper.
Simmer covered
to
40 minutes.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: extra chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in oil.
Mix all other ingredients well, then add melted chocolate morsels and oil to other mixture. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350° or until tested done.

title: broccoli with cashews
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft and pale yellow.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over cooked broccoli and sprinkle with cashews. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: savory sauerkraut
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast for one
directions: Fry apples with margarine in nonstick skillet until softened. Crumble bread into beaten egg.
Mix until bread is soaked like French toast.
Pour into skillet with apples.
Add cinnamon and sugar (or Sweet 'N Low).
Continue to fry until bread is toasty and apples are turning brown and are done.

title: oriental chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat water to boiling in a 3 qt. saucepan.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir in everything except egg and Ramen noodles (including bouillon and seasoning packet from Ramen noodles). Stir, wait a few minutes for vegetables to heat up.
Crack egg and drop yolk and white into soup while stirring constantly.
Break up Ramen noodles and add to soup.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until noodles are softened.
Serve immediately. (Does not keep well overnight since noodles thicken.)

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes with milk and blend in other ingredients.
Once smooth, transfer to a casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Allow room in dish for potatoes to rise.

title: spanish rice ii
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with oil.
Add rice to hot oil and stir until brown.
Add onion, pepper, tomato puree and garlic salt.
Add enough water to cover rice mixture.
As the rice cooks, continue adding water until rice is tender.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place meat in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Add vegetables.
Blend salt, sugar and tapioca.
Sprinkle over meat and vegetables.
Add tomato juice.
Cover pan with foil, sealing tightly around edges.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole, pouring tomatoes over top.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: layered banana-pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef
in
microwave safe colander, place in microwave safe bowl, stir in onions.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes until no longer pink.
Discard drippings.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart Pyrex casserole
dish
and
mix remaining ingredients. Cover and microwave on Roast for 15 to 20 minutes.	Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, undrained fruit, 1 cup coconut and eggs. Blend and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: italian bake
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Pour in Ragu and heat up.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Grate cheeses.
In casserole dish, layer hamburger mixture, noodles, then cheeses; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cheeses should be golden on top.

title: baked carrots
directions: Slice fresh carrots lengthwise. Cook in water until tender. Place carrots in baking dish. Combine other ingredients and pour over carrots. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: super tasty basic meatloaf
directions: In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup ketchup, tomato juice, salt, peppers, eggs, breadcrumbs, onion and 2 teaspoons mustard.
Mix thoroughly.
Add ground beef.
Mix. Press beef into a 5 X 5 loaf pan.
Combine 1/4 cup ketchup, 1/2 teaspoon mustard and brown sugar and spread over meatloaf.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.

title: filled barquettes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon thawed spinach souffle into barquettes and bake on greased baking sheets until golden (about 10 minutes).
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Beat 20 minutes; it will double in amount.
Fold in 1 (9 ounce) container of Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Put in freezer. Serve from freezer as needed.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pastry lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Pour syrup mixture over crackers.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Heat brown sugar, corn syrup and butter to boiling over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat. Stir in cream and vanilla. Cool completely; stir just before serving.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates and baking powder and set aside to cool.
Beat egg yolks and sugar and add to cool dates.
Add flour, nuts, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in loaf pan (8 x 4 x 2-inch) in 350° oven for 1 hour or more.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly and put in greased 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: christmas holly
directions: Rub hands in butter.
Melt together marshmallows and oleo. Add coloring and vanilla.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Put spoon in handle in center and form wreath shape.
Add cinnamon candies for holly berries.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: grandma's german potato dressing
directions: Grind first 6 ingredients together.
Add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Pack loosely in turkey. Excess stuffing may be placed in aluminum foil and baked in end of roaster with turkey, or placed in greased pan, covered with foil and bake separately.
When ready to serve, remove from turkey and pan and place in heavy lightly oiled skillet over medium heat.
Add enough broth or water to make a thick stirring consistency.
Stir occasionally until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Put layer in bottom of baking dish. Add half of chicken.
Heat soups in saucepot.
Pour half over chicken.
Repeat layers using half of remaining dressing mix, all of chicken and all of the soup.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Bake at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes, until done.

title: sweet potato nuggets
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape 1/4 mixture around each marshmallow.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until marshmallows begin to ooze.
Makes 8 servings.
May be frozen and baked when needed.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1 pint of strawberries and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Put the other pint in the pie.
In a saucepan put the 2 cups of strawberries and water.
Add cornstarch and sugar.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat eggs; add oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix well.
Mixture can be stored in refrigerator in a covered container for 6 weeks.
Do not stir when you spoon batter into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugar, then extract.
Ice cake before frosting cools.

title: the best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure the rum is really good, pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again.

title: homemade soup
directions: Brown beef.
I cut up a cheap piece of steak or roast (ground meat is fine).
I don't use stew meat.
Add to your Dutch oven or large boiler in which you have boiled several carrots.
The carrots should have been boiled only for a short time.
Add cut up potatoes, tomatoes and cream-style corn.
Boil a cup of water; add bouillon cubes.
Add to soup mix.
Cut up okra is good to add if you have it.
Also add celery and onion (cut up, but not real fine).
Boil for 5 or 10 minutes.
Simmer for an hour or two.
I serve with cornbread.

title: decadent chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Remove layers and let cool.
Brush brandy over layers.
Spread preserves between cake layers.
Melt remaining morsels, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; gradually stir in sour cream, blending well. Spread frosting on cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover and chill.

title: trash
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels and nuts in a bowl. Set aside. Heat the chips in a microwave bowl for 1 minute or until melted. Stir. Pour over the cereal mixture, stirring until well coated. Spread on waxed paper to cool. After completely cooled, break into small pieces.

title: renee's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Layer with cheese and crackers between layers and on top.
Or pour into a baking dish.
Put crackers and cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: jellied waldorf salad
directions: Combine diced apples, celery, nut meats and mayonnaise. Prepare lime jello according to directions on package.
When slightly thickened, fold in mixture and turn into 1-quart mold or individual molds.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow squash cakes with tomato
directions: In a large bowl, blend squash, onion, egg, flour, salt, 1 teaspoon garlic and pinch of pepper.

In a large frying pan, heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat. Spoon 1/4 cup squash mixture per pancake (it should hold 3 cakes), pressing to form 3-inch rounds. Cook until edges are lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Turn and cook until edges on the other side are lightly browned (3 minutes more).
Remove to plate and keep warm.
Repeat with remaining squash using 2 teaspoons oil per batch.
When all cakes are cooked, add tomato, the remaining garlic and oil to pan and cook 2 minutes. Serve cakes with dollop of tomato.

title: cream pie mix
directions: Scald milk and cream in top of double boiler.

Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt. Add to scalded milk and cook until smooth and thick. Cook 15 minutes longer, constantly stirring. Stir a small amount into egg yolks that have been beaten. Return to double boiler and cook a few minutes longer.
You can use bananas or 1/2 cup coconut, if you wish.
Use beaten egg whites for topping, if you wish.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat 2 cups or 1 can crushed pineapple, sugar and lemon juice. Boil a minute or two.
Soak Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water for 10 minutes, then add to the hot pineapple mixture.
When cool and beginning to set, add the grated American cheese, pimento and green pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the whipped cream.
Stir thoroughly; let set.

title: peg's apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into 8-inch pan.
Combine together all other ingredients until crumbs.
Put on top of apples.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.

title: lazy jane casserole
directions: Combine beef, wine, consomme soup, salt, pepper and onion in casserole.
Mix flour with crumbs.
Stir into casserole mixture.

title: scandinavian icebox cake
directions: No Cooking, no baking.
Drain pineapple, crush zwieback into crumbs and mix butter.
Make layers of zwieback and pineapple, starting and ending with zwieback.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Serve lots of whipped cream and a garnish of more crushed pineapple in the center.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10-inch).
Cook broccoli or cauliflower in salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth for 1 minute with beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center adn edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: roasted sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drizzle olive oil on top.
Sprinkle all other ingredients.
Put in roasting pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; turn.
Bake 45 minutes more.
Turn oven to 425° for last 10 minutes, until potatoes are nice and crisp.

title: lucas' potato soup(serves 8)
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, then place in the distilled water and boil until approximately over half done (approximately 10 minutes). Now cut and dice celery to a fine texture and add to water and potatoes.
At the same time, add semolina pasta and veggie spirals. Boil until celery is tender.
At this time, the semolina pasta and veggie spirals will be done.
Take off stove and add soy milk, sea salt and some parsley, if desired.

title: bacon tomato dip(or bacon tomato sandwiches)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on white bread circles directly before serving, otherwise your bread will get hard.
OR you can serve with corn chips.
You can also serve this recipe hot with toasted bread squares.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple chunks in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese; place over pineapple.
Mix crackers and margarine; sprinkle over. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Stir chili hot beans, tomatoes with onions, chili powder and Tabasco sauce into ground beef.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in this order:

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Dry the potato slices in a cloth. Rub the garlic around the inside of a baking dish.
Butter the dish well, using a third of the butter and arrange the potato slices in layers.
Season the layers with salt and sprinkle top lightly with nutmeg.
Pour over the cream.
Dot the remaining butter over the surface.
Bake in the oven for 10 minutes.
Then lower the heat to 350° and cook for another hour.
For less rich potatoes, use milk.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned blueberry cake
directions: Add egg, sugar and oil.
Mix together. Sift all dry ingredients.
Add to mixture alternating with sour milk.
Add blueberries by folding into mixture.
Will make a large cake or thicker small one. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes depending on size of pan used.

title: crunch candy
directions: Mix together and spread on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Melt 1 pound chocolate and pour over mixture, coating all the ingredients.
Chill, then break up in different size pieces.

title: never fail beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper beef to taste and roll in flour.
Brown in a skillet with oil or shortening; drain.
Place beef in a casserole dish with the vegetables.

title: banana cake supreme
directions: Beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add the melted butter and stir vigorously.
Add mashed bananas and soda.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into batter.
Dust the raisins and chopped nuts with a little flour and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Let cool and spread hot Vanilla Glaze over top of cake.

title: indonesian spice chicken(also good with pork chops)
directions: Combine onion, garlic, oil, lemon juice, red pepper, ginger and black pepper.
Place chicken into plastic bag in deep bowl. Add marinade.
Tie bag closed.
Refrigerate several hours.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Pat chicken dry.
Place on grill, bone side down over medium hot coals.
Grill 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn often and brush with marinade.
(May be baked in 350° oven until meat is tender.
I leave marinade with meat when baking in oven.)

title: microwave chicken
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in pie pan.
Melt margarine; stir in garlic powder.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip in garlic/margarine mixture.
Roll in crumbs.
Sprinkle in paprika. Arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Rearrange chicken (do not turn).
Cover. Cook on High 8 to 12 minutes until done.

title: curried rice
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups water and salt in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and water absorbed.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over raisins.
Let stand 1 minute.
Drain raisins; set aside.
Combine butter and curry powder, stirring to blend.
Stir curry mixture, raisins and walnuts into cooked rice.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil; remove from heat immediately.
Add oats, coconut, salt and chocolate.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
(If batter is too sticky, add more oats until it is the correct consistency.)
Cool.
No baking needed!

title: good stuff
directions: Crush potato chips and chunk wieners.
Place in casserole alternating layers of corn chips and wieners.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: mississippi omelet
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1 slice of cheese together in a pan over low heat.
Stir until cooked done.
Spoon into plate immediately.
Place other 2 slices of cheese on egg omelet.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Make a well in center of mixture and set aside.
Stir together buttermilk and undrained can of chili peppers.
Add buttermilk mixture all at once to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Turn out dough on floured surface.
Quickly knead dough by gently folding and pressing dough 10 to 12 strokes or until dough is smooth.
Pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Dip cutter into flour between each cut.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter.

title: herbed hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 4 to 6 patties. Broil for 7 minutes, turning once.
Serve on egg twist buns.

title: johnny marzetti casserole
directions: Saute vegetables and mushrooms in oleo.
Add olives, hamburger, soup, sauce and noodles.
Mix and pour into a large baking dish.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Tastes like pizza in a casserole.

title: shrimp spread for crackers
directions: Boil or steam shrimp.
Cut into small pieces.
Marinate in juice of lemons at least 2 hours.
Add Worcestershire sauce, grated onion and mayonnaise.
Give some time for flavors to meld.

title: baked barley and mushrooms
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients. Cover. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.

title: microwave buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda, in 4 to 5-quart dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes again.
Take out and stir.
Microwave again on High for 4 minutes.
Take out and add 1 teaspoon baking soda until foamy.
Microwave for 1 more minute on High.
Whip until tacky (about 1 minute).
Drop by teaspoons on foil.
Cool.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Cook pasta, using package directions; drain.
Brown ground chuck in heavy 5-quart saucepan, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add olive oil, onion, carrots and hot pepper flakes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, basil, rosemary and oregano. Bring to boil.
Add beans and pasta; mix gently.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Garnish servings with cheese and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: polish dill pickles
directions: Layer the pickles and dill in a pickling crock (or plastic container).
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl until salt is dissolved.
Pour mixture in crock.
Add a little water if required to cover cukes and weigh the cukes down with a plate.
Cover.
Will be pickled in 3 to 4 days at room temperature.
Keep in fridge afterward for several weeks.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, wheat flour, yeast and salt; mix well.
Heat milk, water, honey and shortening until warm (115° to 120°).
Add to flour mixture; add egg.
Mix at low speed until moistened, then at medium speed 3 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour.
Knead on floured board about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled (1 hour).
Punch dough down. Divide into 2 parts.
Shape into loaves and let rise in bread pans until double (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: perfect roast beef
directions: Wash roast and pat dry.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roast at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 15 minutes per pound.
Comes out medium-rare.
Adjust for more well done.

title: jello salad
directions: Stir cottage cheese and dry jello until mixed well.
Add all the next ingredients in order.
Mix well and chill.

title: easy chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups milk and the soup in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Stir in chicken, mixed vegetables and mushrooms.
Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add syrup, salt and vanilla and beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Gel cranberries.
Dilute jello in water; pour over top.
Mix. Refrigerate until gelled.
Blend cream cheese and crushed pineapple (drained) with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put on top of set jello.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Filling:
Blend
cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and
1 teaspoon
vanilla;
beat
until lemon color.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25	minutes
in
13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: cucumber cream cheese spread
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Add next three ingredients and mix well.
Stir in onion and cucumber.
Put in covered container. Chill one hour before serving.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain and add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce and heat thoroughly. Turn into an 8 inch square casserole dish.
Cut cheese into strips and sprinkle over meat.
Top with biscuits.
(If desired, use 6 biscuits in casserole and bake remainder.)

title: strawberry-rhubarb cake
directions: Mix
rhubarb, sugar, marshmallows and jello.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch
greased bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed and pour over
rhubarb
mix.
Bake
1 hour at 350°.	Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: finnish cranberry pudding
directions: Cook the 2 cups of cranberries in just enough water to almost cover.
Cook and mash until juice is out.
Put through a strainer and add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Put back on the stove, add the sugar and bring to a boil.
Add a scant 1/3 cup of Cream of Wheat slowly to thicken.
Let cool and then whip.
Serve with cream.

title: easy veggie pie
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Mix broccoli, onion, mushrooms and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a 4-quart cooker on high until forms a ball (test in cold water).
In a large mixing bowl beat 3 egg whites stiff.
Pour first mixture into egg whites slowly, beating on high speed.
Keep beating until mixture can be kneaded like dough.
On countertop sift confectioners sugar.
Roll out and then spread peanut butter on.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cool and slice.

title: cheese-scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender; drain.
In saucepan, gently cook onion in margarine 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, then milk.
Cook, stirring until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange layer of carrots, then layer of cheese.
Repeat until all are used, ending with carrots.
Pour on sauce; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(Can be made the day before and refrigerated.)

title: blueberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar until light and fluffy. Fold in Cool Whip. Slice bananas onto crust. Top with cream cheese mixture, then spread pie filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: mulled cider
directions: In medium saucepan, heat the cider with the allspice, cloves and cinnamon and cook over moderate heat for 6 minutes.
Add the sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook for 6 more minutes.
Serve piping hot in small punch glasses.

title: mixed vegetable curry
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Deep fry potato on high heat until golden and tender.
Then deep fry carrots until tender. Drain and set aside vegetables.

title: poor man's lobster dip
directions: Cut up butter and put in bottom of microwave dish.
Add seafood chunks (in bite size chunks) on top.
Add cream cheese, cut into cubes.
Microwave 10 minutes.
Stir; if not creamy, add more time.
Can bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir and cook 5 minutes more. Serve with French bread, cut into cubes.

title: mini fruit cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift first 6 ingredients together and add the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
(I spooned batter into small paper bonbon size baking and party cups and placed cherry on top.)
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, sprinkle with sherry or brandy, if desired.
(I prefer them without the booze.)
Makes about 12 dozen miniature cakes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube to boiling.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and do not drain.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Boil until berries pop.
Add Jell-O. Cool.
Add last 4 ingredients and stir.
Chill.

title: pudding cake crowd pleaser(must be made 24 hours in advance!)
directions: Great way to use graham crackers that are no longer crispy. Prepare vanilla pudding and allow to thicken while you line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with a single layer of crackers.

Pour vanilla pudding slowly over crackers and spread to pan edges. Prepare chocolate pudding and set aside to thicken while you place another single layer of crackers on top of the vanilla pudding. Gently pour chocolate over crackers and spread to pan edges.
Now place another layer of crackers and cover completely with Cool Whip.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill about 24 hours before serving.

title: monty's ham salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together until smooth. Add 1 cup flour and 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Repeat adding flour and eggs until eggs and flour are gone.
Add flavor; pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan about 20 minutes.
Turn out on rack.

title: best ever apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Mix.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken, saving 2 cups broth.
In a large pan, saute together onion, celery, green pepper.
Add chicken, broth, soup, rice and soy sauce.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and cashews just before serving.
